[[L'Oréal]] Paris named Lopez their new Global Ambassador and the face of their brands, including EverPure hair care, Preference hair color and Youth Code skin care. Her EverSleek hair care ads made their debut in early 2011, to coincide with the release of ''Love?'' and her debut as a judge on ''American Idol''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.realstylenetwork.com/blogs/beauty/2010/12/jennifer-lopez-named-loreal-paris-global-ambassador |title=Jennifer Lopez Named L'Oreal Paris Global Ambassador |publisher=Real Style Network |date=December 3, 2010 |access-date=August 8, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130425055005/http://www.realstylenetwork.com/blogs/beauty/2010/12/jennifer-lopez-named-loreal-paris-global-ambassador |archive-date=April 25, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> To further promote her comeback, in February, [[Gillette Mach3|Venus]] chose Lopez as their new Global Ambassador.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.realstylenetwork.com/blogs/beauty/2011/02/jennifer-lopez-is-the-new-venus-global-ambassador |title=Jennifer Lopez Is The New Venus Global Ambassador |publisher=Real Style Network |date=February 3, 2011 |access-date=August 8, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110913034756/http://www.realstylenetwork.com/blogs/beauty/2011/02/jennifer-lopez-is-the-new-venus-global-ambassador/ |archive-date=September 13, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Lopez's comeback single "[[On the Floor]]" was released later that same month. The song topped the charts across the globe, becoming one of the most successful singles of the year.<ref name="Digital report 2012">{{cite web|title=IFPI digital music report 2012 – key facts and figures |url=http://ifpi.com/content/library/DMR2012_key_facts_and_figures.pdf |publisher=[[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]] |access-date=January 23, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121030053448/http://ifpi.com/content/library/DMR2012_key_facts_and_figures.pdf |archive-date=October 30, 2012 }}</ref> The song also became her highest-charting single commercially as a lead artist, as well as her most successful airplay hit on [[contemporary hit radio]], since "Jenny from the Block".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/471634/beastie-boys-score-no-2-debut-on-billboard-200-adele-holds-at-no-1 |title=Beastie Boys Score No. 2 Debut on Billboard 200, Adele Holds at No. 1 |work=Billboard |last=Caulfield |first=Keith |date=May 11, 2011 |access-date=May 29, 2011}}</ref> ''Love?'', which was released in April, was a moderate commercial success, and was viewed as a humble comeback from Lopez, as many had considered her recording career over.<ref name=lovereview>{{cite web|last=Copsey|first=Robert|title=Jennifer Lopez: 'Love?'|url=https://www.digitalspy.com.au/music/albumreviews/a317729/jennifer-lopez-love.html|work=Digital Spy|access-date=January 29, 2012|date=May 4, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110505234750/http://www.digitalspy.com.au/music/albumreviews/a317729/jennifer-lopez-love.html|archive-date=May 5, 2011|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Lopez launched her next fragrance Love and Light in July, exclusively on HSN. 51,000 bottles of the fragrance were sold at its premiere, becoming Lopez's most successful fragrance launch to date, making over $2.9 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.instyle.com/2011/07/07/jennifer-lopez-hsn-love-and-light-sales |title=Jennifer Lopez HSN – Love & Light |work=InStyle |date=July 7, 2011 |access-date=August 8, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120321015622/http://news.instyle.com/2011/07/07/jennifer-lopez-hsn-love-and-light-sales/ |archive-date=March 21, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In September, Lopez launched the [[Jennifer Lopez Collection]], a clothing and accessories line for [[Kohl's]] with [[Tommy Hilfiger]].<ref name="goahead">{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez – Jennifer Lopez's Fashion Line To Go Ahead|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/jennifer-lopezs-fashion-line-to-go-ahead_1233187|publisher=Contactmusic News |access-date=February 5, 2012|date=July 19, 2011}}</ref> In addition to the clothing line, she also launched the Jennifer Lopez Home Collection, featuring bedding, towels and luggage.<ref name="Lopez Previews Her Kohl's Collection">{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez Previews Her Kohl's Collection|url=http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2011/08/12/jennifer-lopez-for-kohls|publisher=Style News|access-date=January 31, 2012|date=August 12, 2011|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120620124214/http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2011/08/12/jennifer-lopez-for-kohls/|archive-date=June 20, 2012}}</ref> Later that same month [[Fiat]], an Italian automobile manufacturer, enlisted Lopez to promote their products, including the [[Fiat 500 (2007)|2012 Fiat 500 Cabrio]]. Olivier Francois, the [[Chrysler]] chief marketing officer, stated that she "fits perfectly with the brand".<ref>{{cite web |last=Lienert |first=Anita |url=http://www.insideline.com/fiat/500/2012/fiat-and-jennifer-lopez-hook-up.html |title=Fiat and Jennifer Lopez Hook Up |publisher=[[Insideline]] |date=September 13, 2011 |access-date=August 8, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120125080306/http://www.insideline.com/fiat/500/2012/fiat-and-jennifer-lopez-hook-up.html |archive-date=January 25, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

[[File:Jennifer Lopez 12, 2012.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Lopez performing during her [[Dance Again World Tour]] in Paris, France, October 2012]]

In January 2012, Lopez returned as a judge on the [[American Idol (season 11)|eleventh season]] of ''American Idol'', earning a reported $20 million.<ref name="Forbes2">{{cite news|author=Hannah Elliott |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hannahelliott/2012/05/16/the-real-american-idol-how-j-lo-got-her-mojo-back/ |title=The Real American Idol: How J.Lo Got Her Mojo Back |work=[[Forbes]] |date=April 18, 2012 |access-date=May 24, 2012}}</ref> Later that same month, a new talent show, ''[[Q'Viva! The Chosen|¡Q'Viva! The Chosen]]'', created by [[Simon Fuller]] premiered on [[Univision]] and was a hit for the channel.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/jennifer-lopez-marc-anthonys-qviva-250584 | work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] | title=Jennifer Lopez and Marc Anthony's 'Q'Viva: The Chosen': First Broadcast Partners Announced | date=October 19, 2011}}</ref> It followed Lopez, Anthony, and director-choreographer [[Jamie King]] as they travelled across 21 countries in Latin America to find new talent for a [[Las Vegas]] show. On May 18, Lopez returned to the big screen starring alongside an [[ensemble cast]] consisting of [[Cameron Diaz]], [[Elizabeth Banks]], [[Matthew Morrison]] and [[Dennis Quaid]] in the film ''[[What to Expect When You're Expecting (film)|What to Expect When You're Expecting]]'', which is based on the [[What to Expect When You're Expecting|novel of the same name]].<ref name="Lopez">{{cite news|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2011/06/24/jennifer-lopez-what-to-expect-when-youre-expecting |title=Jennifer Lopez signs on for 'What to Expect When You're Expecting'|last=Labrecque|first=Jeff|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=June 24, 2011|access-date=July 23, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110630094618/http://insidemovies.ew.com/2011/06/24/jennifer-lopez-what-to-expect-when-youre-expecting/ |archive-date=June 30, 2011 |url-status=dead}}</ref> In late May, Lopez released her fragrance Glowing by JLo, which she described as an "evolution" of Glow by JLo.<ref name="Huffington">{{cite news|first=Michelle |last=Manetti |url=https://huffingtonpost.com/2012/02/10/glowing-jennifer-lopez-launching-new-fragrance_n_1268972.html |title=Jennifer Lopez Launches 'Glowing' Perfume With Naked Ad, Light-Up Bottle (Photos) |work=[[HuffPost]] |access-date=March 3, 2012 |date=February 10, 2012}}</ref>

Lopez launched the [[Dance Again World Tour]], her first headlining concert tour, on June 14, 2012.<ref name="My Diary May 3">{{cite web |url=http://jenniferlopez.com/blog/post/my-diary|title=My Diary |date=May 3, 2012 |publisher=Jennifer Lopez Website |access-date=May 13, 2012|archive-url=http://www.freezepage.com/1336988633AFEXHXNLRN?url=http://jenniferlopez.com/blog/post/my-diary |archive-date=May 14, 2012}}</ref> It was a lucrative, grossing over $1 million per show.<ref name="Forbes 2013" /> On July 12, she launched [[Teeology]], a luxury [[T-shirt]] [[e-commerce]].<ref>{{cite news |author=Andrea Huspeni |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/jennifer-lopez-to-launch-teeology-2012-7 |title=Jennifer Lopez to Launch Teeology |publisher=Business Insider, Inc. |date=July 12, 2012 |access-date=August 5, 2012}}</ref> Lopez voiced Shira, a saber tooth tiger, in the animated film, ''[[Ice Age: Continental Drift]]'', the fourth film in the ''[[Ice Age (franchise)|Ice Age]]'' franchise.<ref name="Rovi Ice Age 4">{{cite web |first=Jeremy |last=Wheeler |url=http://www.allrovi.com/movies/movie/ice-age-continental-drift-3d-v516738 |title=Ice Age: Continental Drift 3D – Cast, Reviews, Summary, and Awards |publisher=AllRovi |access-date=October 30, 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120128010036/http://www.allrovi.com/movies/movie/ice-age-continental-drift-3d-v516738 |archive-date=January 28, 2012 }}</ref> The film became her highest opening weekend figure, at $46 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sfgate.com/tv/article/Ice-Age-storms-the-weekend-box-office-3708776.php|title=Ice Age storms the weekend box office|date=July 15, 2012|work=San Francisco Chronicle|agency=Associated Press}}</ref>

Lopez's first greatest hits album, ''[[Dance Again... the Hits]]'', was released on July 24, 2012, in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a388349/jennifer-lopez-to-release-dance-again-the-hits-next-month.html |title=Jennifer Lopez to release 'Dance Again: The Hits' next month? |work=Digital Spy |date=June 19, 2012 |access-date=July 10, 2012}}</ref> It was released by Epic Records, as Lopez owed them one final album to end her contract, despite previously announcing that she had fulfilled her contract with the label.<ref name="radio1">{{cite web |url=http://925maxima.radio.com/2012/05/28/jennifer-lopez-interview-new-single-goin-in |title=Jennifer Lopez Talks About Her New Single "Goin' In" |publisher=925maxima Radio |date=May 28, 2012 |access-date=June 23, 2012 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20121216101846/http://925maxima.cbslocal.com/2012/05/28/jennifer-lopez-interview-new-single-goin-in/ |archive-date=December 16, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Lopez, who was going through a divorce with Anthony and the "breakup of a family", felt as if the album's sole single, "[[Dance Again]]", had come to her at the "perfect moment".<ref name="ryaninterview">{{cite web|first=Michael |last=Murray |url=http://ryanseacrest.com/2012/03/30/jennifer-lopez-talks-dance-again-her-upcoming-album-audio/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Talks 'Dance Again' & Her Upcoming 'Greatest Hits' Album |publisher=Ryan Seacrest Productions |date=March 30, 2012 |access-date=March 31, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120402195736/http://ryanseacrest.com/2012/03/30/jennifer-lopez-talks-dance-again-her-upcoming-album-audio/ |archive-date=April 2, 2012 }}</ref><ref name="AOL2">{{cite web|last=Gayles|first=Contessa|title=Jennifer Lopez, Divorce: Real Reason Singer Went on World Tour?|url=http://blog.music.aol.com/2012/12/06/jennifer-lopez-divorce-tour/|publisher=[[AOL|AOL Music Blog]]|access-date=December 7, 2012|date=December 6, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121210020725/http://blog.music.aol.com/2012/12/06/jennifer-lopez-divorce-tour/|archive-date=December 10, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> "Dance Again" and "[[Goin' In]]", a single from the soundtrack of the dance film ''[[Step Up Revolution]]'', both reached the top of the ''Billboard'' Hot Dance Club Songs, giving Lopez her twelfth and thirteenth number one on that chart, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/chartbeat/480578/chart-highlights-gotye-extends-multi-format-chart-success |title=Latest Music News, Band, Artist, Musician & Music Video News |work=Billboard |date=August 6, 2012 |access-date=August 8, 2012}}</ref> [[nuvoTV]] announced in September its premier partnership with Lopez, that will see her work on the creative side of the network, managing marketing and program production with her production company, [[Nuyorican Productions]], as well as periodically appearing in network programming.<ref name="Jennifer Lopez Partnering With NuvoTV">{{cite news|url=https://huffingtonpost.com/2012/09/13/jennifer-lopez-nuvotv_n_1880503.html |title=Jennifer Lopez Partnering With NuvoTV, Takes Equity Stake In Cable Network |work=HuffPost|date=September 13, 2012 |access-date=September 16, 2012 |first=Samreen |last=Hooda}}</ref><ref name="Jennifer Lopez to Take Minority Stake in Cable's Nuvo TV">{{cite news |last=Steinberg |first=Brian |url=http://adage.com/article/media/jennifer-lopez-minority-stake-cable-s-nuvo-tv/237139 |title=Jennifer Lopez to Take Minority Stake in Cable's Nuvo TV |work=[[Advertising Age]] |date=September 12, 2012 |access-date=September 16, 2012}}</ref>

In January 2013, Lopez starred alongside [[Jason Statham]] in the crime thriller ''[[Parker (2013 film)|Parker]]'', in which she played Leslie. Her performance earned positive reviews, with ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' commending the role for giving Lopez "an opportunity to be dramatic, romantic, funny, depressed, euphoric and violent. The audience stays with her all the way".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/sns-201301251600--tms--lizsmittr--x-a20130128-20130128,0,6035496.story |title=Hackford's 'Parker' packs a big punch |newspaper=Chicago Tribune |date=January 28, 2013 |access-date=December 5, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130729082325/http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/sns-201301251600--tms--lizsmittr--x-a20130128-20130128%2C0%2C6035496.story |archive-date=July 29, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The following month, she gained widespread notoriety for wearing a daring black dress at the [[2013 Grammy Awards|Grammy Awards]], which revealed her entire right leg; despite a conservative dress code which had been issued to celebrities in attendance.<ref>{{cite news|author=Christie D'Zurilla |url=https://latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/gossip/la-et-mg-jennifer-lopez-vs-angelina-jolie-leg-grammys-20130210,0,5894431.story |title=Jennifer Lopez vs. Angelina Jolie: Which leg do you love? |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=February 11, 2013 |access-date=April 19, 2013}}</ref> In May, Lopez was announced as the [[chief creative officer]] of nuvoTV. In addition, she founded the mobile phone retail brand [[Viva Móvil]], which is catered specifically for Latinos.<ref>{{cite web |last=Cheng |first=Roger |url=http://reviews.cnet.com/8301-12261_7-57585831-10356022/jennifer-lopez-dishes-on-new-viva-movil-shopping-q-a |title=Jennifer Lopez dishes on new Viva Movil shopping (Q&A) |publisher=Cnet Reviews |date=May 23, 2013 |access-date=May 24, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130528054136/http://reviews.cnet.com/8301-12261_7-57585831-10356022/jennifer-lopez-dishes-on-new-viva-movil-shopping-q-a/ |archive-date=May 28, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> She lobbied for more Hispanic diversity on television,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-22886829 |title=Jennifer Lopez lobbies for more diversity on TV|date=June 13, 2013 |newspaper=BBC News}}</ref> hoping to empower the Latin community in these media ventures, stating: "There's a big revolution going on, it's like a media and cultural revolution of Latinos here in the United States. We're realizing our power. We're realizing that we matter here."<ref name="Latino1">{{cite news |url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2013/06/13/jennifer-lopez-wants-latinos-to-realizing-our-power/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Wants Latinos To Realize Their Power |publisher=Fox News Latino |date=June 13, 2013 |access-date=June 18, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130617154216/http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2013/06/13/jennifer-lopez-wants-latinos-to-realizing-our-power/ |archive-date=June 17, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Inspired by her gay aunt who had recently died, Lopez signed on as executive producer of the television series ''[[The Fosters (2013 TV series)|The Fosters]]'', which is about a same-sex couple raising a family.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://huffingtonpost.com/2013/04/24/jennifer-lopez-declares-the-fosters_n_3149200.html |title=Jennifer Lopez's Lesbian Aunt: Star Says 'The Fosters' TV Show Inspired By Late Relative |work=HuffPost |date=April 24, 2013 |access-date=May 31, 2013}}</ref> The show premiered on [[ABC Family]] on June 3, 2013, and has since been a ratings success for the network.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/06/11/monday-cable-ratings-love-hip-hop-wins-night-wwe-raw-teen-wolf-major-crimes-switched-at-birth-longmire-more/186745/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130614204339/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/06/11/monday-cable-ratings-love-hip-hop-wins-night-wwe-raw-teen-wolf-major-crimes-switched-at-birth-longmire-more/186745/|url-status=dead|archive-date=June 14, 2013|title=Monday Cable Ratings: 'Love & Hip Hop' Wins Night, 'WWE Raw', 'Teen Wolf', 'Major Crimes', 'Switched at Birth', 'Longmire' & More – Ratings |last=Bibel|first=Sara |work=The Numbers |date=June 11, 2013}}</ref> Later that June, Lopez performed at the birthday of [[Turkmenistan]] President [[Gurbanguly Berdymukhamedov]].<ref name="Turkmenistan, Washington Post" /> Doing so, she garnered widespread backlash for performing for the leader of a "repressive, [[authoritarianism|authoritarian regime]]". Her publicist released an apology.<ref name="Turkmenistan, Washington Post">{{cite news|title=Jennifer Lopez apologizes for Turkmenistan performance|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/reliable-source/wp/2013/06/30/jennifer-lopez-sings-for-dictator-paula-deen-loses-cookbook/|work=[[The Washington Post]] |access-date=July 1, 2013|date=June 30, 2013}}</ref> Lopez returned as judge on ''American Idol'' for its [[American Idol (season 13)|thirteenth season]] for a reported salary of $17.5 million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lopez to earn USD 17.5 million for American Idol return|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/lopez-to-earn-usd-17-5-million-for-american-idol-return-113090100045_1.html|work=Business Standard |access-date=September 24, 2013|date=September 1, 2013}}</ref> She was ranked as the fifth highest-paid woman in music for 2013, having earned $45 million.<ref name="Forbes 2013">{{cite news |title=No. 5: Jennifer Lopez ($45 million)|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/eeel45eglhi/no-5-jennifer-lopez-45-million/|work=Forbes |access-date=February 8, 2015}}</ref>

===2014–2017: Television ventures and residency show ===
[[File:Jennifer Lopez at GLAAD Media Awards (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|upright|Lopez at the [[25th GLAAD Media Awards]] in April 2014]]

After the conclusion of her Dance Again World Tour, Lopez began recording her eighth studio album, ''[[A.K.A. (album)|A.K.A.]]'', inspired by her travels.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lopez didn't expect new album so soon|url=http://au.news.yahoo.com/entertainment/a/-/entertainment/17557067/lopez-didnt-expect-new-album-so-soon/|publisher=Yahoo! News |access-date=June 13, 2013|date=June 11, 2013}}{{Dead link|date=November 2015}}</ref> It was released in June 2014 through [[Capitol Records]], experiencing lackluster sales.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lipshutz|first1=Jason|title=Jennifer Lopez's 'A.K.A.' Debut: An Icon Reaches a Crossroads|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6141007/jennifer-lopez-aka-debut-sales-pop-column|website=Billboard |access-date=January 24, 2015|date=June 30, 2014}}</ref> The album produced three singles: "[[I Luh Ya Papi]]", which features [[French Montana]], "[[First Love (Jennifer Lopez song)|First Love]]", and "[[Booty (Jennifer Lopez song)|Booty]]", featuring Pitbull or rapper [[Iggy Azalea]]. "Booty" debuted inside the top twenty in the United States, making it her second-highest debut on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 after "On the Floor".<ref name=hot100>{{cite news|last1=Trust|first1=Gary|title=Meghan Trainor No. 1 On Hot 100, Jeremih Hits Top 10, Jennifer Lopez Debuts|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6259336/hot-100-meghan-trainor-jeremih-jennifer-lopez|access-date=September 25, 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=September 24, 2014}}</ref> In April, the official song for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] performed by [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]], Lopez and Brazilian recording artist [[Claudia Leitte]], "[[We Are One (Ole Ola)]]", was released. She was ranked as the sixth highest-paid woman in music for the year, earning $37 million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez ($37 million)|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/eeel45emikk/6-jennifer-lopez-37-million/|website=Forbes |access-date=January 25, 2015}}</ref> In November 2014, Lopez partnered with Endless Jewelry, designing a range of new jewelry products.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cheng|first1=Andrea|title=Here's Your First Look at Jennifer Lopez's New Jewelry Designs|url=http://www.instyle.com/news/heres-your-first-look-jennifer-lopezs-new-jewelry-designs|website=InStyle |access-date=September 21, 2015|date=January 15, 2015}}</ref> That month, she also released first her book, ''[[True Love (book)|True Love]]'', which became a [[The New York Times Best Seller list|''New York Times'' best-seller]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cowles|first1=Gregory|title=Inside the List|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/23/books/review/inside-the-list.html|website=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=December 10, 2016|date=November 14, 2014}}</ref>

January 2015 saw the release of ''[[The Boy Next Door (film)|The Boy Next Door]]'', an erotic thriller that Lopez both co-produced and starred in as a high school teacher who becomes involved with a student, which eventually leads to his dangerous obsession with her.<ref name="HuffPost Latino">{{cite news |last1=Moreno|first1=Carolina|title=Jennifer Lopez On Why Her New Movie Is 'Breaking Down' Stereotypes|url=https://huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/23/jennifer-lopez-ryan-guzman_n_6373936.html|work=HuffPost|access-date=December 27, 2014|date=December 23, 2014}}</ref> The film received negative reviews from critics.<ref>{{cite news|title='Strange Magic,' 'Mortdecai,' 'The Boy Next Door': Review Revue|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2015/01/23/strange-magic-mortdecai-the-boy-next-door-review-revue/|access-date=January 24, 2015|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |date=January 23, 2015}}</ref> Despite this, it became her most successful opening at the box office for a live action film since ''Monster-in-Law'',<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mendelson|first1=Scott|title=Friday Box Office: Johnny Depp's 'Mortdecai' Flops, Jennifer Lopez's 'Boy Next Door' Scores|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2015/01/24/friday-box-office-johnny-depps-mortdecai-flops-jennifer-lopezs-boy-next-door-scores/|website=Forbes |access-date=January 26, 2015|date=January 24, 2015}}</ref> and ultimately grossed over $53 million at the global box office, against a production budget of $4 million.<ref name="Box Office Mojo">{{cite web|title=The Boy Next Door (2015)|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=boynextdoor.htm|website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |access-date=March 10, 2015}}</ref> Lopez had a voice role in the animated feature ''[[Home (2015 comedy film)|Home]]'', alongside [[Steve Martin]], [[Jim Parsons]], and [[Rihanna]], and released in March 2015.<ref name="Martin & Lopez">{{cite web|last=Dickey|first=Josh|title=Jennifer Lopez, Steve Martin Board DreamWorks Animation's 'Home' (Exclusive)|url=https://thewrap.com/steve-martin-jennifer-lopez-board-dreamworks-animations-home-exclusive/|publisher=The Wrap News Inc|access-date=October 4, 2013|date=October 3, 2013}}</ref> She contributed the single "[[Feel the Light]]" to the film's official soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/jennifer-lopez/news/premiere-watch-jennifer-lopezs-cute-feel-the-light-video |title=Exclusive! Watch Jennifer Lopez's Cute 'Feel The Light' Video |publisher=[[MTV]] |last=Pell |first=Michael |date=February 24, 2015 |access-date=February 26, 2015 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226114331/http://www.mtv.co.uk/jennifer-lopez/news/premiere-watch-jennifer-lopezs-cute-feel-the-light-video |archive-date=February 26, 2015 }}</ref> Lopez also starred in the independent drama film ''[[Lila & Eve]]'', alongside [[Viola Davis]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Seidman|first=Robert|title=Viola Davis & Jennifer Lopez To Star In Indie Film 'Lila and Eve' Produced By Lifetime Films & A+E Studios|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/01/27/viola-davis-jennifer-lopez-to-star-in-indie-film-lila-and-eve-produced-by-lifetime-films-ae-studios/232388/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223131446/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/01/27/viola-davis-jennifer-lopez-to-star-in-indie-film-lila-and-eve-produced-by-lifetime-films-ae-studios/232388/|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 23, 2014|work=[[Zap2it]] |access-date=March 11, 2014|date=January 27, 2014}}</ref> With annual earnings of $28.5 million, she was ranked as the seventh highest-paid woman in music for 2015.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Falcone|first1=Dana Rose|title=Katy Perry beats out Taylor Swift to become 2015's highest-paid woman in music|url=https://ew.com/article/2015/11/05/katy-perry-highest-paid-woman-music-2015|website=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=March 26, 2016}}</ref>

Lopez starred as Detective [[Harlee Santos]] in [[NBC]]'s crime drama series ''[[Shades of Blue (TV series)|Shades of Blue]]'' (also serving as an [[executive producer]]), a single mother and police detective in New York City who goes undercover for the FBI to investigate her own squad.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/nbc-orders-cop-drama-starring-jennifer-lopez-to-series-1201116116/ |title=NBC Orders Cop Drama Starring Jennifer Lopez to Series |work=Variety |date=February 21, 2014 |access-date=July 20, 2014}}</ref> It premiered on January 7, 2016, giving the network its most-watched Thursday debut in seven years with 8.6 million viewers.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Maglio|first1=Tony|title=Ratings: J Lo's 'Shades of Blue' Is Most-Watched NBC Thursday Debut in 7 Years|url=https://thewrap.com/jennifer-lopez-shades-of-blue-ray-liotta-american-idol-nbc-tv-ratings-fox/|website=TheWrap|access-date=January 8, 2016}}</ref> Lopez's performance received positive reviews.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Paskin|first1=Willa|title=Shades of Blue|work=Slate|date=January 6, 2016|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/arts/television/2016/01/shades_of_blue_on_nbc_starring_jennifer_lopez_reviewed.html|access-date=January 7, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Tucker|first1=Ken|title='Shades of Blue' Review: J. Lo Gets Low-Down|url=https://www.yahoo.com/tv/shades-of-blue-review-jennifer-lopez-140321526.html|publisher=Yahoo!|access-date=January 7, 2016|date=January 7, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Rotten Tomatoes TV|shades-of-blue/s01}}</ref> ''Shades of Blue'' was renewed for a second season, which premiered in March 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/jennifer-lopezs-shades-blue-renewed-862516|title=Jennifer Lopez's 'Shades of Blue' Renewed at NBC|last=O'Connell|first=Michael|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 5, 2016|access-date=February 5, 2016}}</ref> That same month, the series was renewed for a third season.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Stanhope|first1=Kate|title=Jennifer Lopez Drama ''Shades of Blue'' Renewed for Season 3 at NBC|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/shades-blue-renewed-season-3-987123|access-date=March 18, 2017|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 17, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170318124930/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/shades-blue-renewed-season-3-987123|archive-date=March 18, 2017|location=United States}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=Jennifer Lopez Cop Drama ''Shades Of Blue'' Renewed For Season 3 By NBC|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/shades-of-blue-renewed-season-3-nbc-jennifer-lopez-1202045962/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=March 17, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170318125057/http://deadline.com/2017/03/shades-of-blue-renewed-season-3-nbc-jennifer-lopez-1202045962/|archive-date=March 18, 2017|location=United States|date=March 17, 2017}}</ref> In May 2015, she announced her [[Las Vegas]] residency concert show, which commenced on January 20, 2016, the first of twenty initial dates. Titled [[All I Have (residency)|All I Have]], it takes place at [[Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino|Planet Hollywood]]'s [[Zappos Theater]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stutz|first1=Colin|title=Jennifer Lopez Announces Las Vegas Residency|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6561397/jennifer-lopez-announces-las-vegas-residency|work=Billboard |access-date=May 18, 2015|date=May 12, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez Reveals Title and Artwork for Vegas Show|url=http://lasvegas.cbslocal.com/2015/09/20/jennifer-lopez-reveals-title-and-artwork-for-vegas-show/|website=CBS Las Vegas|access-date=September 20, 2015|date=September 20, 2015}}</ref> The residency has been lucrative,<ref name="2016 Earnings" /> and Lopez signed a three-year contract which saw her perform 120 shows.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Leach|first1=Robin|title=Review: J.Lo inks three-year contract; Pitbull, Ne-Yo, Ja Rule join her onstage|url=http://lasvegassun.com/vegasdeluxe/2016/jan/21/review-jlo-inks-three-year-contract-as-pitbull-ne/|website=[[Las Vegas Sun]]|access-date=June 29, 2016|date=January 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160702144836/http://lasvegassun.com/vegasdeluxe/2016/jan/21/review-jlo-inks-three-year-contract-as-pitbull-ne/|archive-date=July 2, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The residency concluded on September 29, 2018, having grossed over $100 million in ticket sales during its three-year run.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chiu |first1=Melody |title=Jennifer Lopez Surpasses $100 Million in Ticket Sales as She Wraps Star-Studded Vegas Residency |url=https://people.com/music/jennifer-lopez-wraps-all-i-have-las-vegas-residency/ |website=[[People (magazine)|People]] |access-date=October 1, 2018 |date=September 30, 2018}}</ref> In March 2016, six years after announcing her departure, she announced her return to Epic Records, signing a multi-album deal with the label.<ref name="New Epic Deal">{{cite news|title=Jennifer Lopez Signs New Deal With Epic Records |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6897352/jennifer-lopez-signs-new-deal-with-epic-records |access-date=March 2, 2016 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |agency=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=March 2, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304094959/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6897352/jennifer-lopez-signs-new-deal-with-epic-records |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |location=United States |url-status=live }}</ref> Her first single since returning to Epic, "[[Ain't Your Mama]]", was released the following month.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rosen|first1=Christopher|title=Jennifer Lopez teases new single 'Ain't Your Mama'|url=https://ew.com/article/2016/04/04/jennifer-lopez-aint-your-mama|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=April 7, 2016|date=April 4, 2016}}</ref> With earnings of $39.5 million, she was among the highest-paid female artists from June 2015 to June 2016.<ref name="2016 Earnings">{{cite web|title=Taylor Swift tops chart of highest paid female artists|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/nov/03/taylor-swift-tops-forbes-chart-highest-paid-female-artists-adele|website=[[The Guardian]]|access-date=December 6, 2016|date=November 3, 2016}}</ref> Lopez reprised her voice role as Shira in the animated film ''[[Ice Age: Collision Course]]'', which was released in July 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ice Age: Collision Course|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=iceage5.htm|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|access-date=June 30, 2016}}</ref>

In collaboration with [[Giuseppe Zanotti]], Lopez designed a capsule collection of shoes and jewelry. ''Giuseppe for Jennifer Lopez'' launched in January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Underwood|first1=Khalea|title=Jennifer Lopez Teams Up With Giuseppe Zanotti for 'Bad Ass High Heels' Collection|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-style/news/jennifer-lopez-and-giuseppe-zanotti-will-release-shoes-w431171|website=[[Us Weekly]]|access-date=July 28, 2016|date=July 27, 2016}}</ref> In July 2016, Lopez announced a new dance competition series entitled ''[[World of Dance (TV series)|World of Dance]]'', for which she serves as an executive producer and judge. Created in partnership with [[World of Dance]], the series was greenlit by NBC with a straight-to-series order for ten episodes.<ref name="Variety July 2016">{{cite web|last1=Wagmeister|first1=Elizabeth|title=NBC Greenlights Reality Dance Competition Series from Jennifer Lopez|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/world-of-dance-jennifer-lopez-competition-reality-nbc-1201817499/|website=Variety|access-date=July 23, 2016|date=July 19, 2016}}</ref> ''World of Dance'' premiered on May 30, 2017; with 9.7 million viewers, it became the most-watched premiere for a summer alternative series in nine years.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Maglio|first1=Tony|title=Ratings: J Lo's 'World of Dance' Scores Big Premiere After 'AGT'|url=https://thewrap.com/world-dance-americas-got-talent-agt-ratings/|website=[[TheWrap]]|publisher=The Wrap News, Inc.|access-date=June 1, 2017|date=May 31, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=O'Connell|first1=Michael|title=TV Ratings: NBC's 'World of Dance' Scores a Big Post-'Talent' Debut|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/tv-ratings-nbcs-world-dance-scores-post-talent-debut-1008894|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|access-date=June 1, 2017|date=May 31, 2017}}</ref> According to ''Forbes'', Lopez was the eleventh highest-paid female celebrity between June 2016 and June 2017, with earnings of $38 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=11. Jennifer Lopez ($38 million) – Highest-Paid Female Celebrities Of 2017|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/59306b53a7ea434078d4a3a4/11-jennifer-lopez-38-mill/|website=[[Forbes]]|access-date=June 26, 2017}}</ref> Lopez had announced in October 2016 that she was working on a second full-length Spanish album, which was set to be released through [[Sony Music Latin]], with Marc Anthony serving as an executive producer.<ref name="Billboard Spanish Album 2016">{{cite web|last1=Cobo|first1=Leila|title=Jennifer Lopez to Release Spanish Album, Executive Produced by Marc Anthony: Exclusive|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7533475/jennifer-lopez-spanish-album-marc-anthony-executive-producer|website=Billboard|access-date=October 7, 2016|date=October 6, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Cobo|first1=Leila|title=Jennifer Lopez to Premiere New Single at Macy's 4th of July Celebration|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7850314/jennifer-lopez-jlo-macys-gente-de-zona-marc-anthony-fourth-of-july-2017|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=July 4, 2017|date=July 4, 2017}}</ref> It was to be titled ''Por Primera Vez'', which translates to ''For the First Time'' in English.<ref name="RS Video">{{cite web|last1=Kreps|first1=Daniel|title=See Jennifer Lopez Throw Subway Dance Party in 'Amor, Amor, Amor' Video|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/see-jennifer-lopez-throw-subway-dance-party-in-new-video-w511575|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=November 12, 2017|date=November 12, 2017}}</ref> The album, which never materialized,<ref>{{cite web |last1=McDermott |first1=Maeve |title=The 15 albums we can't wait to hear in 2019 |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2018/12/21/15-albums-we-cant-wait-hear-2019/23793 |website=[[USA Today]] |access-date=September 14, 2019 |date=December 21, 2018}}</ref> produced two singles: "[[Ni Tú Ni Yo]]" (featuring Cuban [[reggaeton]] group [[Gente de Zona]])<ref>{{cite web|title=Exclusive: Jennifer Lopez Talks 'World Of Dance' & Her New Album (Video)|url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/videos/exclusive-jennifer-lopez-talks-world-of-dance-her-new-album/|website=[[Access Hollywood]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal]]|access-date=July 4, 2017|date=June 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Iasimone|first1=Ashley|title=Jennifer Lopez Releases New Song 'Ni Tu Ni Yo': Listen|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7857055/jennifer-lopez-ni-tu-ni-yo-listen|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=July 4, 2017|date=July 4, 2017}}</ref> and "[[Amor, Amor, Amor]]" featuring [[Wisin]].<ref name="RS Video" />

===2018–present: ''Hustlers'' and Super Bowl LIV halftime show ===

[[File:Jennifer Lopez Live during Its my party tour.jpg|thumb|left|upright|200px|Lopez performing during her [[It's My Party (tour)|It's My Party]] tour in July 2019]]

In April 2018, Lopez launched her limited-edition makeup collection in collaboration with [[Inglot Cosmetics]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Inglot Cosmetics Announces Collaboration With Jennifer Lopez|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/inglot-cosmetics-announces-collaboration-with-jennifer-lopez-300623507.html|publisher=[[PR Newswire]]|access-date=April 9, 2018|date=April 5, 2018}}</ref> That month, she was named one of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]''{{'}}s [[Time 100|100 most influential people in the world]],<ref name="Time 100">{{cite web|last1=Reilly|first1=Katie|title=Jennifer Lopez and Shawn Mendes to Perform at the 2018 TIME 100 Gala|url=http://time.com/5246023/time-100-2018-jennifer-lopez-shawn-mendes/|website=[[Time (magazine)|Time]].|access-date=April 30, 2018|date=April 19, 2018}}</ref> and released a new Spanish single, "[[El Anillo]]".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Machin|first1=Jennifer|title=Jennifer Lopez Premieres 'El Anillo' at the Billboard Latin Music Awards: Watch|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8390274/jennifer-lopez-el-anillo-billboard-latin-music-awards-performance|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=April 28, 2018|date=April 26, 2018}}</ref> The following month, she released a bilingual single titled "[[Dinero (Jennifer Lopez song)|Dinero]]", featuring [[DJ Khaled]] and [[Cardi B]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Jones|first=Abby|title=Jennifer Lopez Drops Bilingual Banger 'Dinero' With DJ Khaled & Cardi B: Listen|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8456507/jennifer-lopez-dinero-dj-khaled-cardi-b-new-song|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=May 18, 2018|date=May 17, 2018}}</ref> With earnings of $47 million between June 2017 and June 2018, ''Forbes'' listed Lopez as the sixth highest-paid woman in music.<ref>{{cite web |last1=O'Malley Greenburg |first1=Zack |title=The World's Highest-Paid Women In Music 2018 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2018/11/19/highest-paid-women-in-music-2018-katy-perry-taylor-swift-beyonce/#6c814816a243 |website=[[Forbes]] |access-date=December 12, 2018 |date=November 19, 2018}}</ref> In December 2018, Lopez starred in the comedy film ''[[Second Act (film)|Second Act]]'', directed by [[Peter Segal]]; she also produced the film,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Galuppo|first1=Mia|title=Jennifer Lopez to Star in Romantic Comedy 'Second Act' for STX|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/jennifer-lopez-star-romantic-comedy-second-act-stx-1015976|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|access-date=June 22, 2017|date=June 22, 2017}}</ref> and recorded the single "[[Limitless (Jennifer Lopez song)|Limitless]]" for its soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/amas/8479114/jennifer-lopez-limitless-performance-2018-american-music-awards-watch |title=Jennifer Lopez Performs 'Limitless' at the 2018 American Music Awards: Watch |last=Lyndsey Havens |date=September 10, 2018 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=December 13, 2018}}</ref> ''Second Act'' earned mixed reviews from critics,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Schaffstall |first1=Katherine |title='Second Act': What the Critics Are Saying |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/second-act-review-roundup-what-critics-are-saying-1171068 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=February 14, 2019 |date=December 20, 2018}}</ref> but performed well at the box office, grossing over $72.2 million worldwide with a production budget of $16 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=secondact.htm|title=Second Act (2018)|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|access-date=February 10, 2019}}</ref>

In February 2019, Lopez announced that she will be embarking on her first concert tour in nearly seven years to celebrate her upcoming 50th birthday. Titled [[It's My Party (tour)|It's My Party]], the international tour ran from June to August, grossing an estimated $54.7 million from thirty-eight shows.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Setoodeh |first1=Ramin |title=How Jennifer Lopez Learned to Dance Again |url=https://variety.com/2019/music/features/jennifer-lopez-hustlers-its-my-party-the-godmother-1203313001/ |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |access-date=September 9, 2019 |date=2019}}</ref> In March, alongside her fiancé [[Alex Rodriguez]], Lopez launched a collection of sunglasses with the brand Quay Australia.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hamanaka |first1=Kari |title=Quay Nabs Deal With Jennifer Lopez, Alex Rodriguez on Eyewear Collaboration |url=https://wwd.com/accessories-news/eyewear/quay-collaborates-with-jennifer-lopez-alex-rodriguez-on-eyewear-1203087404/ |website=[[Women's Wear Daily]] |access-date=April 18, 2019 |date=March 20, 2019}}</ref> The following month, she premiered the single "[[Medicine (Jennifer Lopez song)|Medicine]]" featuring French Montana, her first release through [[L.A. Reid]]'s Hitco Entertainment label.<ref>{{cite news |author1=Live Nation Entertainment |author-link1=Live Nation Entertainment |title=World's Hottest Entertainer Jennifer Lopez Reveals Tantalizing Details of North American It's My Party Tour to Celebrate Milestone Birthday with Fans |url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/worlds-hottest-entertainer-jennifer-lopez-reveals-tantalizing-details-of-north-american-its-my-party-tour-to-celebrate-milestone-birthday-with-fans-300816892.html |access-date=March 23, 2019 |work=[[PR Newswire]] |publisher=[[Cision Inc.]] |date=March 22, 2019 |location=United States |language=en }}</ref>

Lopez next starred in the film ''[[Hustlers (film)|Hustlers]]'' (2019), for which she also served as an [[executive producer]], and which grossed over US$100 million in North American box office receipts alone. Directed by [[Lorene Scafaria]], the film is inspired by a true story, following a group of [[Manhattan]] [[stripper]]s who con wealthy men.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marieclaire.com/celebrity/a26141514/jennifer-lopez-constance-wu-hustlers/|title=J.Lo and Constance Wu Will Star in a Movie About Savvy Former Strippers|last=Wood|first=Lucy|date=2019-02-05|website=Marie Claire|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-14}}</ref><ref>[https://www.msn.com/en-us/entertainment/celebrity/jennifer-lopez-shrugs-off-the-rain-for-manhattan-night-shoot-of-star-studded-stripper-revenge-movie-hustlers/ar-AAATccI?li=BBnbfcL&ocid=iehp] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190504144035/http://www.msn.com/en-us/entertainment/celebrity/jennifer-lopez-shrugs-off-the-rain-for-manhattan-night-shoot-of-star-studded-stripper-revenge-movie-hustlers/ar-AAATccI%3Fli%3DBBnbfcL%26ocid%3Diehp |date=May 4, 2019 }} Accessed May 4, 2019.</ref> Lopez's portrayal of a veteran stripper in ''Hustlers'' garnered acclaim from critics, with some deeming it the best performance of her acting career.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Campbell |first1=Christopher |title=Hustlers First Reviews: Jennifer Lopez Is Oscar-Worthy in the Surprise Hit of the Toronto International Film Fest |url=https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/article/hustlers-first-reviews-jennifer-lopez-gives-an-oscar-worthy-turn-in-the-surprise-hit-of-toronto-film-fest/ |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |access-date=September 9, 2019 |date=September 8, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Yang |first1=Rachel |title=Hustlers reviews are in: Jennifer Lopez amazes in one of this year's best films |url=https://ew.com/movie-reviews/2019/09/08/hustlers-reviews-are-in-jennifer-lopez-amazes-in-one-of-this-years-best-films/ |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=September 9, 2019 |date=September 8, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Sharf |first1=Zack |title=Jennifer Lopez Overwhelmed by 'Hustlers' Oscar Buzz: 'It Brings Tears to Your Eyes' |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/09/jennifer-lopez-hustlers-oscar-buzz-reaction-1202172137/ |publisher=[[IndieWire]] |access-date=September 9, 2019 |date=September 9, 2019}}</ref> The film also gave Lopez her highest opening weekend at the box office for a live action film (grossing $33.2 million),<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mendelson |first1=Scott |title='Hustlers' Box Office: Jennifer Lopez And Constance Wu Break Records With Huge $33 Million Weekend |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/09/15/hustlers-jennifer-lopez-weekend-box-office-33m-constance-wu-keke-palmer-lili-reinhart-cardi-b-lizzo-stx-oscars/#56f043266a13 |website=[[Forbes]] |access-date=September 15, 2019 |date=September 15, 2019}}</ref> and garnered her nominations for Best Supporting Actress at the [[Golden Globe Awards]], [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s, [[Critics' Choice Movie Awards]] and [[Independent Spirit Awards]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=B. Vary |first1=Adam |title=Academy Awards Barely Escape a Reprise of #OscarsSoWhite |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/oscarssowhite-2020-oscars-diversity-1203463343/ |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |access-date=January 31, 2020 |date=January 13, 2020}}</ref> The success of ''Hustlers'' has been regarded by various media outlets as a comeback for Lopez.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McClintock |first1=Pamela |title='Hustlers': Jennifer Lopez Poised for Major Box Office Comeback |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hustlers-jennifer-lopez-poised-major-box-office-comeback-1238824 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=September 22, 2019 |date=September 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hornaday |first1=Ann |title=J-Lo makes a commanding comeback in the sexually charged caper flick 'Hustlers' |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/j-lo-makes-a-commanding-comeback-in-the-sexually-charged-caper-flick-hustlers/2019/09/10/9d859264-d31d-11e9-9610-fb56c5522e1c_story.html?arc404=true |website=[[The Washington Post]] |access-date=September 22, 2019 |date=September 10, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Mendelson |first1=Scott |title='Hustlers' Tops Box Office With Record $13 Million Friday, But 'The Goldfinch' Bombs |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/09/14/friday-box-office-hustlers-13m-jennifer-lopez-constance-wu-keke-palmer-lili-reinhart-cardi-b-lizzo-stx-goldfinch-nicole-kidman/#63dc632e4edf |website=[[Forbes]] |access-date=September 22, 2019 |date=September 14, 2019}}</ref> Also in September 2019, Lopez modeled an updated version of her [[Green Versace dress of Jennifer Lopez|Green Versace dress]] at [[Milan Fashion Week]]; her appearance generated $31.8 million in total media impact value.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jennifer Lopez revives dress behind the invention of Google Images |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-49780020 |website=[[BBC News]] |access-date=December 30, 2019 |date=September 21, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Lockwood |first1=Lisa |title=Jennifer Lopez Gives Big Boost to Media Impact Value at Milan Fashion Week |url=https://wwd.com/business-news/media/jennifer-lopez-media-impact-value-milan-1203320114/ |website=[[Women's Wear Daily]] |access-date=September 30, 2019 |date=September 27, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190930233801/https://wwd.com/business-news/media/jennifer-lopez-media-impact-value-milan-1203320114/ |archive-date=September 30, 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Following this, she launched her twenty-fifth fragrance, which is titled Promise,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bitmead |first1=Charlotte |title=Jennifer Lopez Launches Her 25th Fragrance 'Promise' |url=https://www.elle.com/uk/beauty/body-and-physical-health/a29262421/jennifer-lopez-promise-perfume/ |website=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]] |access-date=October 1, 2019 |date=September 27, 2019}}</ref> and was announced as the global face of the [[Coach New York|Coach]] brand.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Intner |first1=Katie |title=Jennifer Lopez Named the New Global Face of Coach |url=https://people.com/style/jennifer-lopez-named-the-new-global-face-of-coach/ |website=[[People (magazine)|People]] |access-date=December 30, 2019 |date=September 30, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230004209/https://people.com/style/jennifer-lopez-named-the-new-global-face-of-coach/ |archive-date=December 30, 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

In September 2019, it was announced that Lopez would co-headline the [[Super Bowl LIV halftime show]] alongside [[Shakira]], which took place on February 2, 2020, in [[Miami, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Jennifer Lopez and Shakira to headline Super Bowl 2020 half-time show |url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2019/sep/26/jennifer-lopez-and-shakira-to-headline-super-bowl-2020-halftime-show |website=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=September 26, 2019 |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Gonzalez |first1=Sandra |title=Jennifer Lopez and Shakira to headline Super Bowl halftime show |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/09/26/entertainment/jennifer-lopez-shakira-trnd/index.html |publisher=[[CNN]] |access-date=September 26, 2019 |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref> Her daughter, Emme Maribel Muñiz, also made an appearance at the show.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Yang |first1=Rachel |title=Jennifer Lopez's daughter Emme, 11, joins her on stage during Super Bowl halftime show |url=https://ew.com/music/2020/02/02/jennifer-lopez-daughter-emme-super-bowl-halftime-show/ |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=June 22, 2020 |date=February 2, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.univision.com/famosos/todo-lo-que-sabemos-del-show-de-jennifer-lopez-y-shakira-en-el-super-bowl-liv-y-las-sorpresas-fotos|title=Todo lo que sabemos del show de Jennifer López y Shakira en el Super Bowl LIV... ¿Y las sorpresas?|last=Univision|website=Univision|language=es|access-date=2020-02-03}}</ref> Lopez executive produced and appeared in an episode of ''[[List of Quibi original programming|Thanks a Million]]'', a series with a "[[pay it forward]]" theme which premiered on [[Quibi]] in April 2020.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tapp |first1=Tom |title=Jennifer Lopez's 'Thanks A Million' Renewed For Season 2 By Quibi – Watch The Trailer |url=https://deadline.com/video/jennifer-lopezs-thanks-a-million-renewed-season-two-quibi/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=January 23, 2021 |date=May 29, 2020}}</ref> That month, Lopez also appeared in the television special ''[[One World: Together at Home]]'', performing a rendition of "[[People (Barbra Streisand song)|People]]" by [[Barbra Streisand]], due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9361325/jennifer-lopez-people-one-world-together-at-home|title=Jennifer Lopez Channels Barbra Streisand, Performing 'People' for 'One World' Concert: Watch|work=Billboard|date=April 18, 2020|access-date=May 19, 2020}}</ref> In September, she released a two-song collaboration with Colombian singer [[Maluma]], "[[Pa' Ti + Lonely]]". Both songs will be featured on the soundtrack for her upcoming film, ''[[Marry Me (2022 film)|Marry Me]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/9455024/jennifer-lopez-maluma-pa-ti-lonely-music-video|title=Jennifer Lopez Teams Up With Maluma for Fiery Two-Part Video 'Pa' Ti' & 'Lonely'|date=September 24, 2020|website=Billboard|access-date=September 24, 2020|first=Jessica|last=Roiz}}</ref> That December, Lopez headlined the entertainment segment of ''[[Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve|Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve with Ryan Seacrest]]'' in [[Times Square]]; her set list during the performance included her single "[[In the Morning (Jennifer Lopez song)|In the Morning]]" and a cover of the 1973 [[classic rock]] ballad "[[Dream On (Aerosmith song)|Dream On]]" by [[Aerosmith]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/index.php/articles/columns/pop/9506047/jennifer-lopez-new-years-rockin-eve-2021-video|title=Jennifer Lopez Delivers Powerful 'New Year's Rockin' Eve' Performance: 'We Made It'|author=Mitchell Peters|website=Billboard|date=January 1, 2021|access-date=January 2, 2021}}</ref>

In January 2021, Lopez launched her skincare line, JLo Beauty.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lee |first1=Amy |title=Jennifer Lopez's Skincare Line JLo Beauty Is Here! |url=https://www.etonline.com/jennifer-lopezs-skincare-line-jlo-beauty-is-here-151905 |website=[[Entertainment Tonight]] |access-date=January 3, 2021 |date=January 1, 2021}}</ref> That month, she performed at the [[Inauguration of Joe Biden|inauguration]] of President [[Joe Biden]] in Washington, D.C., where she sang "[[This Land Is Your Land]]" and "[[America the Beautiful]]", while also reciting the last phrase of the [[Pledge of Allegiance]] in Spanish.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gold |first1=Michael |title=Jennifer Lopez sang classic tributes to America at the inauguration |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/20/us/jennifer-lopez-inauguration.html |website=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=January 20, 2021 |date=January 20, 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Melas |first1=Chloe |title=Lady Gaga and Jennifer Lopez perform at the inauguration |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2021/01/20/entertainment/jennifer-lopez-inauguration/index.html |publisher=[[CNN]] |access-date=January 20, 2021 |date=January 20, 2021}}</ref> In June 2021, it was announced that Lopez (through Nuyorican Productions) had signed a multi-year deal with [[Netflix]] to produce a range of films and television shows.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jennifer Lopez signs multi-year production deal with Netflix |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/jennifer-lopez-signs-multi-year-production-deal-netflix-rcna1135 |website=[[NBC News]] |access-date=June 15, 2021 |date=June 9, 2021}}</ref> The following month, she released a Spanish single titled "[[Cambia el Paso]]", a collaboration with [[Rauw Alejandro]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zemler |first1=Emily |title=Hear Jennifer Lopez and Rauw Alejandro Team Up on ‘Cambia El Paso’ |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/jennifer-lopez-rauw-alejandro-cambia-el-paso-1192890/ |website=[[Rolling Stone]] |access-date=July 7, 2021 |date=July 5, 2021}}</ref>

====Upcoming projects====
Lopez will next star in ''[[Marry Me (2022 film)|Marry Me]]'' opposite [[Owen Wilson]] for [[Universal Pictures]], which is set to be released on February 11, 2022.<ref name="D'Alessandro">{{Cite web|last1=D'Alessandro|first1=Anthony|date=2021-02-08|title=Jennifer Lopez Movie 'Marry Me' Has Wedding Date Postponed|url=https://deadline.com/2021/02/jennifer-lopez-romantic-comedy-marry-me-postpones-wedding-date-1234689912/|access-date=2021-02-09|website=Deadline|language=en-US}}</ref> She is  attached to star as drug lord [[Griselda Blanco]] in ''The Godmother'' for [[STX Entertainment]], which will focus on the "rise and fall" of Blanco. She will also serve as an executive producer for the film, which is currently in development.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Vlessing|first1=Etan|title=Jennifer Lopez to Star in, Produce True-Life Drug Lord Drama 'The Godmother'|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/amp/news/jennifer-lopez-star-produce-drug-lord-drama-godmother-1226911|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|access-date=July 25, 2019|date=July 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726180824/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/amp/news/jennifer-lopez-star-produce-drug-lord-drama-godmother-1226911|archive-date=July 26, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Lopez will produce and star in four other films in development: the action-comedy ''[[Shotgun Wedding (2022 film)|Shotgun Wedding]]'',<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |title=Jennifer Lopez And Armie Hammer To Star in Lionsgate's 'Shotgun Wedding' |url=https://deadline.com/2020/10/jennifer-lopez-armie-hammer-lionsgates-shotgun-wedding-1234603858/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=December 19, 2020 |date=October 27, 2020}}</ref> and three films for [[Netflix]] including an adaption of [[Kathe Koja]]'s novel ''The Cipher'',<ref>{{Cite web|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|date=2020-12-17|title=Jennifer Lopez Teaming With Netflix For Adaptation Of Novel 'The Cipher'|url=https://deadline.com/2020/12/jennifer-lopez-teaming-with-netflix-for-adaptation-of-novel-the-cipher-1234658440/|access-date=December 18, 2020|website=Deadline|language=en-US}}</ref> the action feature ''The Mother'' (directed by [[Niki Caro]]),<ref>{{cite web |last1=D'Alessandro |first1=Anthony |title=Jennifer Lopez To Star & Produce Action Pic 'The Mother' At Netflix, Niki Caro In Talks To Direct |url=https://deadline.com/2021/02/jennifer-lopez-netflix-movie-the-mother-mulan-niki-caro-to-direct-1234684653/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=February 2, 2021 |date=February 1, 2021}}</ref> and the [[Science fiction film|sci-fi]] thriller ''Atlas'' (directed by [[Brad Peyton]]).<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |title=Jennifer Lopez To Star In Netflix’s Sci-Fi Thriller ‘Atlas’ With Brad Peyton Directing |url=https://deadline.com/2021/06/jennifer-lopez-netflixs-sci-fi-thriller-atlas-brad-peyton-directing-1234775196/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=June 15, 2021 |format=June 15, 2021}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Lopez was in a nearly decade-long relationship with David Cruz, her high school boyfriend, until the mid-1990s.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez's Late High School Sweetheart David Cruz Was 'Soft-Spoken and Kind' Says Source |url=https://people.com/music/jennifer-lopez-late-ex-david-cruz-kind/ |access-date=11 June 2021 |work=People |language=en}}</ref> She was married to Cuban waiter Ojani Noa from February 1997 until January 1998. In subsequent court cases, Noa was prevented from publishing a book about the marriage<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.smh.com.au/news/people/jlo-wins-payout-from-ex-over-tellall-memoir/2007/08/09/1186530500816.html | title=J-Lo Wins Payout From Ex | access-date=August 28, 2007 |work=The Sydney Morning Herald | date=August 9, 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1528384/20060411/lopez_jennifer.jhtml?headlines=true |title=Jennifer Lopez Sues First Husband To Block Tell-All Book |author=Chris Harris |access-date=January 16, 2007 |publisher=MTV News |date=April 11, 2006}}</ref> and from using private honeymoon footage of Lopez in a documentary.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez Sues Ex over Honeymoon Tape |url=https://people.com/crime/jennifer-lopez-sues-ex-over-honeymoon-tape/ |access-date=20 May 2021 |work=People |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez halts sale of 'intimate' honeymoon tape |url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/jennifer-lopez-halts-sale-of-intimate-honeymoon-tape/4IEWBN6POFBHWRNW36XTX25P24/ |access-date=20 May 2021 |work=NZ Herald |language=en-NZ}}</ref> Lopez had an on-off relationship with record producer and rapper [[Sean Combs]] (then known as "Puff Daddy") from 1999 to early 2001.<ref>{{cite news |title=All of Jennifer Lopez's Famous Loves |url=https://people.com/music/jennifer-lopez-dating-history/ |access-date=20 May 2021 |work=People |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=J. Lo finally dishes on P. Diddy |url=https://ew.com/article/2003/05/26/j-lo-finally-dishes-p-diddy/ |access-date=20 May 2021 |work=EW.com |language=en}}</ref> On the night of December 27, 1999, Lopez and Combs were arrested and charged with criminal possession of a weapon and possession of stolen property, after leaving the scene of a shooting at a [[Times Square]] nightclub. Charges against Lopez were dropped within an hour<ref>{{cite news |title=Puff Daddy Arrested On Weapons Charge After Nightclub Shooting |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/620068/puff-daddy-arrested-on-weapons-charge-after-nightclub-shooting/ |access-date=20 May 2021 |work=MTV News |language=en}}</ref> while Combs was acquitted of all charges at trial in early 2001,<ref>{{cite news |title=Puff Daddy Acquitted |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/story?id=101420&page=1#:~:text=N%20E%20W%20Y%20O%20R%20K%2C%20March%2016,other%20patrons%20scrambling%20for%20cover. |access-date=20 May 2021 |work=ABC News |language=en}}</ref> after which the couple split.<ref name=behind/> Lopez later said that, while she had "cared very much" about Combs, their "crazy, tumultuous" relationship "was always something I knew would end."<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tannenbaum |first1=Emily |title=Jennifer Lopez and Diddy Fans Are Hoping for Reunion After the Rapper Posted Sweet Throwback |url=https://www.glamour.com/story/jennifer-lopez-diddy-throwback |access-date=7 June 2021 |work=Glamour}}</ref><ref name=behind/> Lopez was married to [[Cris Judd]], her former back-up dancer, from September 2001 to June 2002.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jennifer Lopez, husband Cris Judd split after 8 months of marriage|newspaper=San Jose Mercury News |date=June 8, 2002|location=California}}</ref>

Lopez had a relationship with actor and filmmaker [[Ben Affleck]] from mid-2002 to early 2004, after meeting on the set of ''Gigli'' in late 2001.<ref>{{cite news|last=Silverman|first=Stephen|title=Ben's Proposal 'Beautiful,' Says Lopez|url=https://people.com/celebrity/bens-proposal-beautiful-says-lopez/|work=[[People (American magazine)|People]] |access-date=February 24, 2019|date=November 11, 2002}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Williams|first=Jeanne|title=J. Lo, Ben make first appearance as fiances|newspaper=[[USA Today]] |date=December 10, 2002|page=2}}</ref> They later worked together on the music video "[[Jenny from the Block]]" and the movie ''Jersey Girl'' (2004).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://articles.latimes.com/2007/oct/14/entertainment/ca-affleck14 |title=Ben Affleck's Roller Coaster Takes a New Turn |first=Patrick |last=Goldstein |work=Los Angeles Times |date=October 14, 2007 |access-date=March 17, 2015 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402211123/http://articles.latimes.com/2007/oct/14/entertainment/ca-affleck14 |archive-date=April 2, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Dam |first1=Julie |title=Jewels of Engagement – Vol. 58 No. 21 |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20138503,00.html |work=People |access-date=April 14, 2017 |date=November 18, 2002 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304101212/http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0%2C%2C20138503%2C00.html |archive-date=March 4, 2016 }}</ref> Their relationship received widespread media coverage.<ref>{{cite news  |title=Why is Bennifer 2.0 so exciting? Because last time, we screwed it up |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/story/2021-05-12/jennifer-lopez-ben-affleck-reunion-bennifer-2-0 |access-date=13 May 2021 |work=Los Angeles Times |date=12 May 2021}}</ref> Tabloids referred to the couple as "Bennifer", a portmanteau which ''Vanity Fair'' described as "the first of that sort of tabloid branding".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2011/09/jennifer-lopez-201109 |title=Jenny Back on the Block |first=Lisa |last=Robinson |work=Vanity Fair |date=August 4, 2011 |access-date=April 14, 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160714073057/http://www.vanityfair.com/news/2011/09/jennifer-lopez-201109 |archive-date=July 14, 2016 }}</ref> They became engaged in November 2002<ref>{{cite news|last1=Silverman |first1=Stephen |title=Ben's Proposal 'Beautiful, Says Lopez |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,624998,00.html |work=People |access-date=April 14, 2017 |date=November 11, 2002 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304001222/http://www.people.com/people/article/0%2C%2C624998%2C00.html |archive-date=March 4, 2016 }}</ref> but their planned wedding on September 14, 2003, was postponed with four days' notice because of "excessive media attention".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Armstrong |first1=Mark |title=Lopez, Affleck Postpone Weekend Wedding |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,624672,00.html |work=People |access-date=April 14, 2017 |date=September 10, 2003 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304072338/http://www.people.com/people/article/0%2C%2C624672%2C00.html |archive-date=March 4, 2016 }}</ref> They ended their engagement in January 2004.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dagostino |first1=Mark |title=Affleck on 'Good Terms' with Lopez |url=http://people.com/celebrity/affleck-on-good-terms-with-lopez/ |work=People |access-date=April 14, 2017 |date=March 9, 2004 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415104106/http://people.com/celebrity/affleck-on-good-terms-with-lopez/ |archive-date=April 15, 2017 }}</ref> Years later, Lopez said Affleck's discomfort with the media scrutiny was one reason for their split<ref name=behind>VH1 Behind the Music, 2010</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez on relationships and tabloids in the "Bennifer Era" |url=https://youtube.com/0uslj8KVT1o |access-date=20 May 2021 |language=en}}</ref> and described it as her "first real heartbreak": "I think different time, different thing, who knows what could’ve happened."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://extratv.com/2016/03/25/jennifer-lopez-reflects-on-relationship-with-ben-affleck/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Reflects on Relationship with Ben Affleck |publisher=Extra TV |date=March 25, 2016 |access-date=April 14, 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221165617/http://extratv.com/2016/03/25/jennifer-lopez-reflects-on-relationship-with-ben-affleck/ |archive-date=December 21, 2016 }}</ref><ref name="Taylor">{{cite news|url=http://pagesix.com/2014/11/06/j-lo-dating-marc-anthony-was-how-i-dealt-with-ben-affleck-split/ |title=J.Lo: Dating Marc Anthony Was How I Dealt with Ben Affleck Split |first=Derrick Bryson |last=Taylor |date=November 6, 2014 |work=[[New York Post]] |access-date=April 14, 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221051520/http://pagesix.com/2014/11/06/j-lo-dating-marc-anthony-was-how-i-dealt-with-ben-affleck-split/ |archive-date=December 21, 2016 }}</ref> Affleck and Lopez remained in contact in the years after their split and spoke positively of each other in the press.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Galloway |first1=Stephen |title=THR Cover: Confessions of Ben Affleck |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/ben-affleck-thr-cover-argo-oscar-377611/ |access-date=20 May 2021 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=2012-10-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez In 'Marie Claire UK': Talks Her Diet, Exes Affleck & Diddy |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/jennifer-lopez-in-marie-c_n_563212 |access-date=16 May 2021 |work=HuffPost |date=4 July 2010 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez thrilled with Ben Affleck's Argo success |url=https://www.hollywood.com/general/jennifer-lopez-thrilled-with-ben-affleck-s-argo-success-59571717/ |access-date=15 May 2021 |work=Hollywood.com |date=16 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Barnes |first1=Brooks |title=On past flame Jennifer Lopez ... "She should have been nominated. She's the real thing. I keep in touch periodically with her and have a lot of respect for her. How awesome is it that she had her biggest hit movie at 50? That's fucking baller." |url=https://twitter.com/brooksbarnesNYT/status/1230538092865474561 |access-date=20 February 2020 |work=@brooksbarnesNYT |date=20 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref> In April 2021, it was reported that Lopez was back together with Affleck again.<ref>{{cite news|title= Ben Affleck and Jennifer Lopez make out at steamy, PDA-packed dinner: Source |url=https://pagesix.com/2021/06/14/ben-affleck-jennifer-lopez-kiss-at-dinner-in-pda-packed-photos/ |access-date=14 June 2021 |work=Page Six.com |language=en}}</ref>

[[File:Time 100 Jennifer Lopez and Marc Anthony.jpg|thumb|right|Anthony and Lopez, 2006]]
Lopez was married to singer [[Marc Anthony]] from June 2004 to July 2011;<ref>{{cite news |author=Andrew Dansby |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/j-lo-marc-anthony-marry-20040607 |title=J.Lo, Marc Anthony Marry &#124; Music News |work=Rolling Stone |date=June 7, 2004 |access-date=April 1, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Wedding highlights J.Lo's true talent: getting us talking|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AASB&p_theme=aasb&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=1031F01295C1112D&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D|access-date=February 25, 2012 | newspaper=Austin American-Statesman |date=June 9, 2004}}</ref> they had previously dated for a few months in the late 1990s.<ref name=behind/> Their wedding took place five months after the end of her relationship with Affleck; she later described it as "a Band-Aid on the cut" and recalled a "rocky start" to the marriage.<ref name="Taylor"/><ref name="youtube.com"/> Lopez gave birth to fraternal twins, Maximilian David and Emme Maribel, on [[Long Island]], in February 2008.<ref name="Welcomes Twins">{{cite news |url=https://people.com/parents/exclusive-jennifer-lopez-marc-anthony-welcome-twins/|date=February 22, 2008|title=EXCLUSIVE: Jennifer Lopez & Marc Anthony Welcome Twins!|work=People |access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://people.com/parents/jennifer-lopez-marc-anthony-reveal-baby-names/|title=Jennifer Lopez & Marc Anthony Reveal Baby Names|work=People|date=February 29, 2008|access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref> ''People'' paid a reported US$6 million for the first photographs of the twins, making them [[List of most expensive celebrity photographs|the most expensive celebrity pictures ever taken]] at the time.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/2009/07/01/michael-jackson-magazine-business-media-jackson.html |title=Jackson Pic Won't Make List Of Priciest Celeb Photos |work=Forbes |access-date=March 21, 2012 |first=Lacey |last=Rose}}</ref> The couple announced their separation in July 2011. Anthony filed for divorce in April 2012<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2012/04/11/jennifer-lopez-divorce-marc-anthony-jlo/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Divorce — Marc Anthony Files Divorce From JLo |publisher=Hollywood Life |date=April 11, 2012 |access-date=June 18, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130618174548/http://hollywoodlife.com/2012/04/11/jennifer-lopez-divorce-marc-anthony-jlo/ |archive-date=June 18, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and it was finalized in June 2014. Lopez retained primary physical custody of the two children.<ref>{{cite web | url= https://tmz.com/2014/06/18/jlo-jennifer-lopez-marc-anthony-divorce-paparazzi/|title=Jennifer Lopez & Marc Anthony's Divorce Has An Anti-Paparazzi Clause| date= June 18, 2014| publisher=[[TMZ.com]]| access-date= April 13, 2016 | quote=The divorce — 2 years in the making —became official Monday [June 16, 2014]. | archive-date=June 19, 2014| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140619005100/http://www.tmz.com/2014/06/18/jlo-jennifer-lopez-marc-anthony-divorce-paparazzi/ | url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/entertainment/jennifer-lopez-gets-her-name-changed-1.2171025 |title=Jennifer Lopez gets her name changed &#124; Entertainment & Showbiz from CTV News |publisher=Ctvnews.ca |date=January 3, 2015 |access-date=May 15, 2015}}</ref>

Lopez had an on-off relationship with her former backup dancer Casper Smart from October 2011 to August 2016.<ref>{{cite news |last=Nudd |first=Tim |url=https://people.com/celebrity/jennifer-lopez-and-casper-smart-split/|title=Jennifer Lopez and Casper Smart Split|work=People |access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Quinn|first1=Dave|title=Jennifer Lopez and Beau 'Casper' Smart Have Split, Says Source: 'It Wasn't Anything Dramatic'|url=https://people.com/celebrity/jennifer-lopez-and-beau-casper-smart-split-source/|work=People|access-date=February 24, 2019|date=August 24, 2016}}</ref> She dated [[New York Yankees]] baseball player [[Alex Rodriguez]] from February 2017 to early 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/music/jennifer-lopez-alex-rodriguez-getting-more-serious-kids-have-met/|title=Jennifer Lopez and Alex Rodriguez 'Getting More Serious' as Source Says Their Kids Have Met: 'Everyone Is Getting Along'|date=April 5, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/03/31/entertainment/jennifer-lopez-and-alex-rodriguez/index.html |title=Alex Rodriguez talks dating Jennifer Lopez|first=Lisa Respers |last=France|work=CNN}}</ref><ref name="Today1">{{cite web |title=Jennifer Lopez and Alex Rodriguez announce breakup in ''Today'' exclusive |url=https://www.today.com/popculture/jennifer-lopez-alex-rodriguez-announce-breakup-today-exclusive-t215133 |website=[[Today (American TV program)|Today]] |publisher=[[NBCUniversal]] |access-date=April 15, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415143521/https://www.today.com/popculture/jennifer-lopez-alex-rodriguez-announce-breakup-today-exclusive-t215133 |archive-date=April 15, 2021 |location=United States |date=April 15, 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> They became engaged in March 2019<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.etonline.com/jennifer-lopez-and-alex-rodriguez-are-engaged-see-her-massive-ring-92838 |title=Jennifer Lopez and Alex Rodriguez Are Engaged -- See Her Massive Ring! |work=Entertainment Tonight |first=Liz |last=Calvario |date=March 9, 2019|access-date=March 10, 2019}}</ref> but postponed their wedding twice due to the pandemic. In response to tabloid speculation about the state of their relationship, they released a statement in March 2021, saying they were "working through some things".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=Emily |title=Inside Alex Rodriguez and Jennifer Lopez’s lavish weddings that never were |url=https://pagesix.com/2021/03/15/inside-alex-rodriguez-and-jennifer-lopezs-weddings-that-never-were/ |access-date=27 May 2021 |work=Page Six |date=2021-03-15}}</ref> They announced the end of their relationship in April 2021.<ref name="Today1" />

In March 2018, Lopez opened up about her own [[Me Too movement]] story of being sexually harassed by a director early on in her career, when she was asked to take her top off during one of her first films.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Desta|first1=Yohana|title=Jennifer Lopez on Her #MeToo Moment: "I Was Terrified"|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/03/jennifer-lopez-me-too-moment-director|access-date=March 15, 2018|magazine=Vanity Fair|date=March 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Reed|first1=Anika|title=Jennifer Lopez reveals her own Me Too story: 'I was terrified'|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2018/03/15/jennifer-lopez-reveals-me-too-story-terrified/428131002/|access-date=March 15, 2018|newspaper=USA Today|date=March 15, 2018}}</ref>

==Other activities==

===Philanthropy===
[[File:P071014AL-0257 (15156063116).jpg|thumb|left|Lopez and First Lady [[Michelle Obama]] posing for a selfie at the [[League of United Latin American Citizens]] National Convention and Exposition in 2014]]

Following the [[September 11 attacks]], Lopez was heavily involved in [[charitable organization|charitable activities]]. Joining various other artists, she was featured on charitable singles such as "[[What's Going On (remix album)|What's Going On]]" and "[[El Ultimo Adios (The Last Goodbye)]]", which benefited people affected by the tragedy.<ref name=africa1>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1450237/ll-cool-j-u2s-edge-whats-going-on.jhtml |title=LL Cool J : LL Cool J, U2's Edge, More Join 'What's Going On' Project – Rhapsody Music Downloads |publisher=MTV News |access-date=March 23, 2012}}</ref><ref name="artistlist">{{cite news |url=http://www.discogs.com/Various-El-Ultimo-Adios-The-Last-Goodbye/release/2075383|title=Complete list of 'El Ultimo Adios' artists |date=May 27, 2011 |publisher=discogs |access-date=February 17, 2010 | first=Stephanie | last=J Stone}}</ref> One dollar from each ticket sold at Lopez and Anthony's [[Jennifer Lopez and Marc Anthony en Concierto|co-headlining North American concert tour]], which grossed an estimated $10 million, was donated to Run for Something Better—a charitable organization supporting [[physical fitness]] programs for children.<ref name="ld1"/><ref>{{cite news|author=Cobo, Leila|date=June 7, 2008|title=Together Again|work=Billboard|volume=120|issue=23 |issn=0006-2510|access-date=May 28, 2012|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_hIEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA10|page=10}}</ref> In February 2007, Lopez was honored with the Artists for Amnesty prize by the human rights organization [[Amnesty International]], for her work in the film ''[[Bordertown (2006 film)|Bordertown]]'', which shed light on the hundreds of [[feminicides in Ciudad Juárez]]. Lopez described it as "one of the world's most shocking and disturbing, underreported crimes against humanity".<ref>{{cite news|title=Amnesty honour for Jennifer Lopez|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/6363913.stm|work=[[BBC News]]|access-date=November 15, 2016|date=February 15, 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Johnson|first1=Reed|title=Mexico's murdered women find a voice in 'Bordertown'|url=https://articles.latimes.com/2007/feb/14/entertainment/et-bordertown14|website=[[Los Angeles Times]]|access-date=November 15, 2016|date=February 14, 2007}}</ref>

In 2009, Lopez launched the [[Lopez Family Foundation]] (originally known as the Maribel Foundation) alongside her sister, Lynda. The nonprofit organization seeks to increase the availability of healthcare for underprivileged women and children, offering a [[telemedicine]] program supported by a partnership with the [[Children's Hospital Los Angeles]]. The foundation has led to the expansion of medical facilities in [[Panama]] and Puerto Rico, and created the Center for a Healthy Childhood at the [[Montefiore Medical Center]] in the Bronx.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Barker|first1=Andrew|title=Jennifer Lopez Aims to Improve Health Care Through Her Foundation|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/features/jennifer-lopez-aims-to-improve-health-care-through-her-foundation-1201323091/|website=Variety|access-date=November 15, 2016|date=October 7, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Rosario|first1=Mariela|title=J.Lo's Medical Scare with Baby Emme Leads Her to Charity|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/celebrity/j-los-medical-scare-baby-emme-leads-her-charity|website=[[Latina (magazine)|Latina]]|publisher=Latina Media Ventures|access-date=November 15, 2016|date=May 12, 2009}}</ref>

In December 2012, Lopez held a charity drive that would affect her three favorite charities: the [[Gloria Wise Boys and Girls Club]], the Children's Hospital of Los Angeles as well as the [[American Red Cross]], mainly benefiting victims of [[Hurricane Sandy]], which devastated parts of her hometown, New York City.<ref name="HSp">{{cite web|last=Moody|first=Nekesa|title=Jennifer Lopez on Holiday Charity Drive and Jenni Rivera: 'It's a Wake-Up Call'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin-notas/1481338/jennifer-lopez-on-holiday-charity-drive-and-jenni-rivera-its-a|work=Billboard |access-date=January 3, 2013|date=December 17, 2012}}</ref> In May 2015, she became the first national celebrity spokesperson for the [[Children's Miracle Network Hospitals]] and the [[BC Children's Hospital Foundation]] (BCCHF), appearing in a campaign entitled "Put Your Money Where the Miracles Are".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Takeuchi|first1=Craig|title=Jennifer Lopez debuts as B.C. Children's Hospital's newest spokesperson|url=https://www.straight.com/blogra/448111/jennifer-lopez-debuts-bc-childrens-hospitals-newest-spokesperson|website=[[The Georgia Straight]]|publisher=Vancouver Free Press|access-date=December 21, 2016|date=May 11, 2015}}</ref> That September, Lopez was announced as the first Global Advocate for Girls and Women at the [[United Nations Foundation]].<ref>{{cite news |title=United Nations Foundation Announces Jennifer Lopez as Global Advocate for Girls and Women|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2015/9/prweb12978264.htm|website=PRWeb |access-date=September 23, 2015|date=September 24, 2015}}</ref> This role sees her mobilizing action to address challenges faced by girls and women around the world, including maternal health care programs, education and violence against women.<ref>{{cite web|title=United Nations Foundation Announces Jennifer Lopez as Global Advocate for Girls and Women|url=http://www.unfoundation.org/news-and-media/press-releases/2015/United-Nations-Foundation-Announces-Jennifer-Lopez-as-Global-Advocate-for-Girls-and-Women.html|publisher=[[United Nations Foundation]]|access-date=November 15, 2016|date=September 23, 2015}}</ref> In September 2017, following [[Hurricane Irma]] and [[Hurricane Maria]], Lopez announced that she would be donating $1 million from the proceeds of her Las Vegas residency to [[humanitarian aid]] for Puerto Rico.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cobo|first1=Leila|title=Jennifer Lopez Donating $1 Million to Aid Hurricane Victims in Puerto Rico|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7973898/jennifer-lopez-alex-rodriguez-donate-1-million-to-puerto-rico-hurricane-maria|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=September 25, 2017|date=September 24, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Connick|first1=Tom|title=Jennifer Lopez donates $1 million to Puerto Rico hurricane victims|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/jennifer-lopez-donates-1-million-puerto-rico-hurricane-victims-2144232|website=[[NME]]|publisher=[[Time Inc. UK]]|access-date=September 25, 2017|date=September 24, 2017}}</ref> Along with ex-husband [[Marc Anthony]], she launched a humanitarian relief campaign entitled Somos Una Voz (English: We Are One Voice), an effort supported by various celebrities to rush supplies to areas affected by Hurricane Maria.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Diaz|first1=Thatiana|title=J.Lo and Marc Anthony Form Alliance with Ed Sheeran and Bruno Mars to Help Puerto Rico|url=https://people.com/chica/marc-anthony-jennifer-lopez-humanitarian-campaign-somos-una-voz/|website=[[People (magazine)|People]]|access-date=September 28, 2017|date=September 27, 2017}}</ref> Lopez and Anthony presented a subsequent concert and telethon for disaster relief, "One Voice: Somos Live!", which raised over $35 million.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Pederson|first1=Erik|title='One Voice: Somos Live!' Disaster-Relief Telethon Raises $35M In Pledges – Update|url=https://deadline.com/2017/10/one-voice-somos-live-telethon-jennifer-lopez-marc-anthony-nbc-telemundo-univision-1202186382/|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=October 17, 2017|date=October 16, 2017}}</ref> She was also among various artists featured on [[Lin-Manuel Miranda]]'s charity single "[[Almost Like Praying]]" which benefits Puerto Rico.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Weldon|first1=Sarah|title=Lin-Manuel Miranda debuts star-studded single for Puerto Rico, 'Almost Like Praying' – listen here|url=https://ew.com/music/2017/10/06/lin-manuel-miranda-more-than-praying-puerto-rico/|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=October 6, 2017|date=October 6, 2017}}</ref>

===Political activism===
[[File:210120-D-WD757-1975 (50860511978) (cropped).jpg|150px|thumb|right|Jennifer Lopez at the [[inauguration of Joe Biden]] in 2021]]
Lopez is an avid supporter of [[LGBT rights]], and has raised millions of dollars for [[HIV/AIDS research]].<ref name="amfAR" /> In June 2013, [[amfAR, The Foundation for AIDS Research|amfAR]] presented Lopez with its humanitarian award for her philanthropic work.<ref name="amfAR">{{cite web|last1=Lipke|first1=David|title=Jennifer Lopez Honored at amfAR's Inspiration Gala|url=http://wwd.com/eye/parties/jennifer-lopez-honored-at-amfars-inspiration-gala-6991956/|website=[[Women's Wear Daily]]|access-date=November 15, 2016|date=June 14, 2013}}</ref> That September, she was awarded the Ally for Equality award presented by the [[Human Rights Campaign]], for her support of the LGBT community.<ref>{{cite web|title=HRC to Honor Jennifer Lopez with Ally for Equality Award at 2013 National Dinner|url=http://www.hrc.org/blog/entry/hrc-to-honor-jennifer-lopez-with-ally-for-equality-award-at-2013-national-d|work=HRC Blog|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|access-date=September 25, 2013|date=September 20, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925143143/http://www.hrc.org/blog/entry/hrc-to-honor-jennifer-lopez-with-ally-for-equality-award-at-2013-national-d|archive-date=September 25, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> The following year, she received the [[GLAAD Vanguard Award]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez Honored at GLAAD Awards|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6051917/jennifer-lopez-honored-at-glaad-awards|website=Billboard|access-date=November 15, 2016|date=April 13, 2014}}</ref> In July 2016, Lopez released a single entitled "[[Love Make the World Go Round]]", a collaboration with Lin-Manuel Miranda, which benefits victims of the [[Orlando nightclub shooting]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Getz|first1=Dana|title=Jennifer Lopez, Lin-Manuel Miranda team for Orlando tribute 'Love Make the World Go Round'|url=https://ew.com/article/2016/07/07/jennifer-lopez-lin-manuel-miranda-orlando-love-make-world-go-round|website=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=July 7, 2016|date=July 7, 2016}}</ref> She was also featured on the song "[[Hands (2016 song)|Hands]]" along with numerous other artists, also benefiting those affected by the Orlando shooting.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Quackenbush|first1=Casey|title=Listen to Britney Spears, Pink, Jennifer Lopez and Others Sing 'Hands' for Orlando|url=http://time.com/4394342/orlando-shooting-tribute-hands-britney-spears-pink-jennifer-lopez/|website=Time|access-date=November 15, 2016|date=July 6, 2016}}</ref> Among numerous other artists, Lopez signed an open letter from [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] magazine to the [[United States Congress]] in 2016, which demanded action on [[gun control]].<ref>{{cite web|title=An Open Letter to Congress from the Music Industry|url=https://www.billboard.com/open-letter/|website=Billboard|access-date=November 19, 2016|date=June 23, 2016}}</ref>

Lopez endorsed President [[Barack Obama]] in his [[Barack Obama presidential campaign, 2012|2012 presidential campaign]], speaking in television advertisements and attending a fundraising event for Obama in Paris.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez in New Obama TV Ad, Wears Hot High-Slit Dress at Fundraiser|url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2012/10/02/jennifer-lopez-in-new-obama-tv-ad-wears-hot-high-slit-dress-at-fundraiser/|website=[[Fox News|Fox News Latino]]|publisher=Fox News Group|access-date=November 19, 2016|date=October 2, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119120609/http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2012/10/02/jennifer-lopez-in-new-obama-tv-ad-wears-hot-high-slit-dress-at-fundraiser/|archive-date=November 19, 2016|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name="Bustle">{{cite web|last1=Donelan|first1=Loretta|title=Hillary Clinton Joins Jennifer Lopez On Stage At The Star's Concert & It's A Great Show Of Support — Video|url=https://www.bustle.com/articles/192276-hillary-clinton-joins-jennifer-lopez-on-stage-at-the-stars-concert-its-a-great-show|website=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]]|access-date=November 19, 2016|date=October 31, 2016}}</ref> She endorsed Democratic presidential nominee [[Hillary Clinton]] in 2016, headlining a free concert in Florida in support of her that October.<ref name="Bustle" /><ref>{{cite web|last1=Mallenbaum|first1=Carly|title=J.Lo takes stage for Hillary Clinton, samples Michelle Obama speech|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2016/10/30/jennifer-lopez-hillary-clinton-miami-concert/93010924/|website=[[USA Today]]|access-date=November 19, 2016|date=October 30, 2016}}</ref> In June 2020, Lopez attended a [[Black Lives Matter]] movement protest in Los Angeles, in connection with the broader [[George Floyd protests]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/music/jennifer-lopez-alex-rodriguez-attend-black-lives-matter-rally/|title=Jennifer Lopez & Alex Rodriguez Attend Black Lives Matter Protest in L.A.: 'We Are Proud to Join'|work=[[People (magazine)|People Magazine]]|author=Todisco, Eric|date=June 8, 2020|access-date=June 9, 2020}}</ref> Lopez has also been an active advocate for the [[Time's Up (movement)|Time's Up movement]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Jimenez|first1=Ashley|title=Jennifer Lopez Delivers #TimesUp Speech In Puerto Rico In Honor of Golden Globes|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/award-shows/jennifer-lopez-timesup-puerto-rico|access-date=March 15, 2018|publisher=Latina Magazine|date=January 7, 2018}}</ref>

==Artistry==
===Influences and musical style===
Lopez has cited [[Madonna]] as her "first big musical influence", explaining "It was all about Madonna for me. She inspired me to want to sing, to dance, to work hard."<ref>{{cite web|last=Miller |first=Prairie |title=NY Rock Interview with Jennifer Lopez |url=http://www.nyrock.com/interviews/2002/lopez_int3.asp |date=December 2002 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20021220071343/http://www.nyrock.com/interviews/2002/lopez_int3.asp |url-status=dead |archive-date=December 20, 2002 |work=NY Rock |access-date=February 12, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stylist.co.uk/people/how-why-this-photo-of-madonna-changed-jennifer-lopezs-life-interview-inspiration-career/25705|title=How this image of Madonna changed Jennifer Lopez's life|work=[[Stylist (magazine)|Stylist]]|date=October 22, 2015|first=Anna|last=Pollitt|access-date=February 20, 2021}}</ref> Other "big influences in [her] life" include [[Tina Turner]], [[James Brown]], and [[Michael Jackson]].<ref name="10 Questions for Lopez">{{cite news |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1673250,00.html |title=10 Questions for Jennifer Lopez |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date=October 18, 2007 |access-date=August 18, 2012|url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071021032212/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1673250,00.html|archive-date=October 21, 2007}}</ref> Growing up, she was influenced by Latin music styles ranging from [[salsa (music)|salsa]] to [[Bachata (music)|bachata]], and artists including [[Celia Cruz]] and [[Tito Puente]]. It was the 1979 hip hop song "[[Rapper's Delight]]" by [[The Sugarhill Gang]] that she said changed her life.<ref name="Woog08">{{harvnb|Woog|2008}}</ref> She was also "hugely inspired in her youth" by [[Rita Moreno]]'s performance in the 1961 musical film ''[[West Side Story (1961 film)|West Side Story]]''.<ref name="LA Times 99" /> Lopez has cited [[Janet Jackson]] as a major inspiration for her own dance and videos, stating that she "probably started dancing" because of Jackson's music video for "[[The Pleasure Principle (song)#Music video|The Pleasure Principle]]".<ref name="timesofindia">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/India-is-on-my-mind-Jennifer-Lopez/articleshow/15631085.cms|title=India is on my mind: Jennifer Lopez|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=Chowdary, Asa|date=August 25, 2012|access-date=August 30, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Schiller |first1=Rebecca |title=Jennifer Lopez on Working With Cardi B, Why Janet Jackson Is an Idol at Billboard Music Awards: Watch |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/8456933/jennifer-lopez-interview-billboard-music-awards-2018-video |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=September 24, 2019 |date=May 20, 2018}}</ref> She looks to the careers of [[Cher]] and [[Diana Ross]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez on how she went to backing dancer to American Idol |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/jennifer-lopez-interview-how-her-role-as-judge-on-ameriacan-idol-has-relaunched-her-career-with-tv-drama-shade-of-blue-and-landed-a-vegas-show-residency-a6826691.html |access-date=16 June 2021 |work=The Independent |date=2016-01-22 |language=en}}</ref> Lopez has also been influenced by younger artists such as [[Lady Gaga]].<ref name="timesofindia"/><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/music/a325337/jennifer-lopez-lady-gaga-inspires-me/|title=Jennifer Lopez: 'Lady GaGa inspires me'
|first=Tom|last=Eames|magazine=Digital Spy|access-date=February 2, 2020|date=June 16, 2011}}</ref>

{{Listen
| pos = right
| filename = Waiting for Tonight.ogg
| title = "Waiting for Tonight"
| description = A twenty-five-second sample of "[[Waiting for Tonight]]". It is a [[dance-pop]] party song that incorporates [[Latin American music|Latin]] and [[Europop|European]] influences.<ref name="Garvin">{{cite web|last1=Blumentrath|first1=Jan|title=Interview with Michael Garvin|url=http://hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview/2005/July24_5_50_38.html|publisher=Hitquarters.com|access-date=January 6, 2015|date=July 24, 2005|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150106161511/http://www.hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview%2F2005%2FJuly24_5_50_38.html|archive-date=January 6, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="Variety" />
}}

According to author Ed Morales in ''The Latin Beat: The Rhythms And Roots Of Latin Music From Bossa Nova To Salsa And Beyond'' (2003), Lopez's music explores the "romantic innocence" of Latin music, while strongly identifying with [[Hip hop music|hip hop]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Morales|first=Ed|title=The Latin Beat: The Rhythms And Roots Of Latin Music From Bossa Nova To Salsa And Beyond|url=https://archive.org/details/latinbeatrhythms00mora_0|url-access=registration|year=2003|publisher=Da Capo Press|isbn=078673020X|page=[https://archive.org/details/latinbeatrhythms00mora_0/page/163 163]}}</ref> Her debut album ''On the 6'' fuses the influence of Latin music with [[contemporary R&B|R&B]] and hip hop, which Lopez described as [[Latin soul]]. To the contrary, Morales described it as "state-of-the-art [[dance pop]]".<ref name="LA Times 99">{{cite news|last=Morales|first=Ed|title=It's Not La Vida Loca to Her|url=https://articles.latimes.com/1999/may/30/entertainment/ca-42339|access-date=March 11, 2012|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=March 30, 1999}}</ref> Dee Lockett, writing for the ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'', stated that songs such as "Waiting for Tonight" made Lopez "arguably the leading artist in the dance-pop movement at the time".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lockett|first1=Dee|title=Once overrated, Jennifer Lopez is now underrated|url=https://stltoday.com/entertainment/music/once-overrated-jennifer-lopez-is-now-underrated/article_0f7d6b7f-36f9-55da-9dc1-b96af888704d.html|website=[[Chicago Tribune]]|access-date=January 8, 2015|date=June 26, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140830073703/http://www.stltoday.com/entertainment/music/once-overrated-jennifer-lopez-is-now-underrated/article_0f7d6b7f-36f9-55da-9dc1-b96af888704d.html|archive-date=August 30, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> While primarily sung in English, she speaks in Spanish and asserts her Latin heritage throughout the album, which is apparent in the song "Let's Get Loud".<ref>{{cite news|last=Tarradell|first=Mario|title=On the 6|newspaper=[[Orlando Sentinel]]|date=June 4, 1999}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Tarradell|first=Mario|title=Pop go the Latin acts Do artists leave heritage behind for crossover success?|newspaper=[[The Dallas Morning News]]|date=June 13, 1999|publisher=[[A. H. Belo Corporation]]}}</ref><ref name="Allmusic On the 6">{{cite web|last=Phares|first=Heather|title=On the 6|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/on-the-6-mw0000238554|publisher=[[Allmusic]]. Rovi Corp.|access-date=April 7, 2013}}</ref> She has also recorded bilingual songs, including the [[Latin pop]] song "[[Cariño (song)|Cariño]]", for her second album ''J.Lo''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Latest From Lopez Made for the Mass Market|newspaper=[[The Miami Herald]]|date=January 26, 2001|page=3}}</ref> A departure from her previous albums, ''This Is Me... Then'' blends 1970s [[soul music|soul]] with "streetwise" hip hop.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Paoletta|first=Michael|title=Reviews and Previews|magazine=Billboard|date=December 7, 2002|volume= 114| issue = 49|page=65|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Og0EAAAAMBAJ&q=Jennifer+Lopez+This+Is+Me...+Then|access-date=April 5, 2013|publisher=Neilsen Business Media}}</ref>

Described as autobiographical,<ref>{{cite web|title=How Jennifer Lopez Turned Hitting 'Rock Bottom' Into A Memoir|url=https://huffingtonpost.com/2014/11/05/jennifer-lopez-_n_6107300.html|website=HuffPost|access-date=January 1, 2015|date=November 5, 2014}}</ref> much of Lopez's music has centered around the "ups and downs" of love.<ref name="LoveMTV" /> The lyrical content of ''This Is Me... Then'' is largely focused on her relationship with [[Ben Affleck]], with the song "Dear Ben" being described as the album's "glowing centerpiece".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://slantmagazine.com/music/review/jennifer-lopez-this-is-me-then/251|title=Jennifer Lopez: This Is Me... Then|last=Cinquemani|first=Sal|work=[[Slant Magazine]]|date=November 20, 2002|access-date=July 24, 2012}}</ref> Her first full-length Spanish-language album, ''Como Ama una Mujer'' features introspective lyrics about romance, heartache and self-loathing.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://boston.com/ae/music/cd_reviews/articles/2007/03/27/lopez_turns_the_lights_down_low |title=Jennifer Lopez goes unabashedly romantic with 'Como Ama una Mujer' |work=[[Boston Globe]] |date=March 27, 2007 |access-date=June 3, 2012 |first=James |last=Reed |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021233216/http://www.boston.com/ae/music/cd_reviews/articles/2007/03/27/lopez_turns_the_lights_down_low/ |archive-date=October 21, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> When explaining her seventh studio album ''Love?'', Lopez stated: "There's still so much to learn and that's why the question mark."<ref name="LoveMTV">{{cite web|last=Dinh|first=James|title=J.Lo Contemplates 'Love' (And Love?) Through The Years|url=http://newsroom.mtv.com/2011/05/03/jlo-contemplates-love-and-love-through-the-years/|publisher=MTV Newsroom|access-date=April 7, 2013|date=May 3, 2011|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130727042918/http://newsroom.mtv.com/2011/05/03/jlo-contemplates-love-and-love-through-the-years/|archive-date=July 27, 2013}}</ref> Other recurrent themes in Lopez's music have included her upbringing in the Bronx<ref name="LA Times 99" /><ref>{{cite news|last=Williott|first=Carl|title=Jennifer Lopez Reminds Us She's The "Same Girl" In Music Video Teaser: Watch|url=http://www.idolator.com/7501076/jennifer-lopez-same-girl-music-video-teaser|access-date=March 8, 2014|newspaper=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=January 13, 2014}}</ref> and [[women's empowerment]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=George|first1=Kat|title=J-Lo is the feminist celebrity icon you never knew you had|url=http://www.dazeddigital.com/music/article/30372/1/j-lo-is-the-feminist-celebrity-icon-you-never-knew-you-had|website=[[Dazed]]|publisher=Waddell Limited|access-date=December 1, 2016|date=March 15, 2016}}</ref>

Critics have considered Lopez's voice to be limited,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/pages/jenniferlopezx18x03x05 |title=Jennifer Lopez – Rebirth – Album Review |publisher=Contactmusic News |access-date=April 1, 2012}}</ref><ref name=vocall>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez finds her voice on new album|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2011/02/02/jennifer-lopez-finds-her-voice-on-new-album/#more-72798|work=Rap-Up |publisher=SpinMedia|access-date=February 12, 2012}}</ref> and overshadowed by the production of her music, while remaining "radio-friendly".<ref>{{cite news |last=Henderling|first=Lisa|title=Revolutions|work=Vibe|date=December 2007|volume= 15| issue = 12|page=107 |issn=1070-4701}}</ref> [[Rob Sheffield]] of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' remarked: "Instead of strained vocal pyrotechnics, Lopez sticks to the understated R&B murmur of a round-the-way superstar who doesn't need to belt because she knows you're already paying attention [...] She makes a little va-va and a whole lot of voom go a long way."<ref name="Rolling">{{cite news |last=Sheffield|first=Rob|title=On the 6 {{!}} Album Reviews|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/on-the-6-19990708|work=Rolling Stone |access-date=April 8, 2013|date=July 8, 1999}}</ref> Meanwhile, [[AllMusic]]'s [[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] called her voice "slight" and wrote: "Lopez was never, ever about singing; she was about style".<ref name="Erlewine">{{cite web|author=Stephen Thomas Erlewine|url={{AllMusic|class=album|id=love-r2142805|pure_url=yes}}|title= Love? – Jennifer Lopez |website=[[AllMusic]]|date=April 19, 2011|access-date=May 3, 2011}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' criticized her vocal performance for lacking the trademark "husky-voiced voluptuousness" she has in her films.<ref name="EW">{{cite news|last=Browne|first=David|title=On the 6 (1999)|url=https://ew.com/ew/article/0,,273612,00.html|work=Entertainment Weekly |access-date=April 7, 2013|date=June 4, 1999}}</ref> [[J. D. Considine]] of ''[[The Baltimore Sun]]'' regards Lopez as having a "breathy" stylistic range, but lacking personality.<ref>{{cite news |last=Considine|first=J.D.|title=Actress Jennifer Lopez can sing, but it isn't enough|newspaper=The Baltimore Sun|date=June 3, 1999 |issn=1930-8965}}</ref>

===Dance and stage===

[[File:The opening ceremony of the FIFA World Cup 2014 13 (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|upright|Lopez performing during the [[2014 FIFA World Cup opening ceremony]] in [[Brazil]]]]

Considered one of dance's "greatest success stories",<ref name="Variety July 2016" /> ''[[Refinery29]]'' ranked Lopez at number two on "11 Of Pop's Most Iconic Dancers" in 2015.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chou |first1=Jessica |title=11 Of Pop's Most Iconic Dancers, Ranked |url=https://www.refinery29.com/2015/07/91060/best-celebrity-dance-moves#slide-10 |website=[[Refinery29]] |access-date=August 10, 2018 |date=July 22, 2015}}</ref> Lopez felt an emotional connection to dance since her youth, when she specialized in ballet, jazz and flamenco.<ref name="Dance buzz">{{cite web|last=Vena |first=Jocelyn |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1659131/jennifer-lopez-on-the-floor-video.jhtml |title=Jennifer Lopez's 'On The Floor' Video Creates 'Dance Buzz' – Music, Celebrity, Artist News |publisher=MTV News |date=March 3, 2011 |access-date=May 31, 2013}}</ref><ref name="Shall We Dance? - Interview">{{cite web|last=Boccard |first=Sophia |title=Jennifer Lopez Interview for Shall We Dance? |url=http://www.thecinemasource.com/blog/interviews/jennifer-lopez-interview-for-shall-we-dance/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110515014355/http://www.thecinemasource.com/blog/interviews/jennifer-lopez-interview-for-shall-we-dance/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=May 15, 2011 |publisher=The Cinema Source |access-date=June 30, 2013 |date=January 28, 2008 }}</ref> Her career commenced on the variety television sketch comedy series ''[[In Living Color]]'', where she was a part of an ethnically diverse dance group known as the [[List of In Living Color cast members#Fly Girls (house dance troupe)|Fly Girls]].<ref name="Hip Hop Dance">{{cite book|last=Rajakumar|first=Mohanalakshmi|title=The American Dancefloor: Hip Hop Dance|year=2012|publisher=Abc-Clio|isbn=978-0313378454|pages=78, 79|edition=Illustrated}}</ref> Since beginning her music career, Lopez has become known for her body-emphasizing music videos, which often include dance routines.<ref>{{cite book|title=Sexual Teens, Sexual Media: Investigating Mediás Influence on Adolescent Sexuality|year=2002|publisher=Routledge|isbn=0805834907|page=260|author1=Jane Delano Brown |author2=Jeanne R. Steele |author3=Kim Walsh-Childers }}</ref> [[CNN]]'s Holly Thomas noted that "Lopez's years of professional dance experience gave her a captivating, commanding presence in her videos."<ref>{{cite web |last1=Thomas |first1=Holly |title=Super Bowl headliner Jennifer Lopez is the star of bouncing back |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/01/31/opinions/super-bowl-jennifer-lopez-comeback-thomas/index.html |publisher=[[CNN]] |access-date=February 1, 2020 |date=January 31, 2020}}</ref> Some of these videos have been the subject of controversy, including "[[Jenny from the Block#Music video|Jenny from the Block]]", "[[Dance Again#Music video|Dance Again]]" and "[[Booty (Jennifer Lopez song)|Booty]]".<ref name="IBT">{{cite news |last=Costanza|first=Ashley Justine|title=Jennifer Lopez's 'Dance Again' Video Stirs Controversy: Her Five Trashiest Videos|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/jennifer-lopezs-dance-again-video-stirs-controversy-her-five-trashiest-videos-435170|work=International Business Times |access-date=June 30, 2013|date=April 9, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Nobody Puts J.Lo's Booty in a Box|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/151961_jennifer_lopez_defends_her_booty_video_talks_scary_car_accident/|website=ETOnline |access-date=December 27, 2014|date=October 1, 2014}}</ref> Her provocatively choreographed music video for "If You Had My Love" allowed Lopez to become a dominant figure on [[MTV]] networks worldwide.<ref>{{cite news |title=Asia Pacific|work=Billboard|date=August 7, 1999|volume= 111| issue = g32 |issn=0006-2510}}</ref> Madeline Roth of MTV wrote: "Her diverse videography encompasses some of the most memorable visuals of the 21st century",<ref>{{cite web |last1=Roth |first1=Madeline |title=Jennifer Lopez, Living Icon, Is Your 2018 VMA Video Vanguard |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3083147/jennifer-lopez-2018-vma-video-vanguard/ |publisher=[[MTV]] |access-date=August 5, 2018 |date=July 31, 2018}}</ref> with ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' writer Brittany Spanos observing that her "dancing skills and ability to toy with her own celebrity have made her videos an important part of the new millennium's pop canon".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Spanos |first1=Brittany |title=5 Artists Who Could Win Future VMA Video Vanguard Awards |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/5-artists-who-could-win-future-vma-video-vanguard-awards-712570/ |website=[[Rolling Stone]] |access-date=August 19, 2018 |date=August 18, 2018}}</ref>

On stage, Lopez is recognized for her showmanship and sex appeal,<ref name="LA Times Vegas">{{cite web|last1=D. Kennery|first1=Gerrick|title=Review Jennifer Lopez gives all she's got – and more – in Vegas|url=https://latimes.com/entertainment/music/posts/la-et-ms-jennifer-lopez-vegas-20160124-story.html|website=[[Los Angeles Times]]|access-date=August 20, 2016|date=January 24, 2016}}</ref> and often includes costumes such as [[bodysuit]]s as part of her performance.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://huffingtonpost.com/2011/11/21/jennifer-lopez-bodysuit-ama_n_1106714.html |title=Jennifer Lopez' Bodysuit At The 2011 American Music Awards (Photos)|work=HuffPost |date=November 21, 2011 |access-date=May 31, 2013 |first=Christina |last=Anderson}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Solomons |first=Tarryn |url=http://www.iol.co.za/tonight/in-your-face-marc-1.1183920 |title=In your face Marc |publisher=IOL Tonight|date=November 22, 2011 |access-date=May 31, 2013}}</ref> Author Priscilla Peña Ovalle stated in ''Dance and the Hollywood Latina: Race, Sex and Stardom'' (2011) that Lopez was one of the Latin stars who "used dance to gain agency as working performers with mainstream careers, yet many of their roles paradoxically racialized and sexualized their bodies".<ref name="Dance Hollywood Latina">{{cite book|last=Peña Ovalle|first=Priscilla|title=Dance and the Hollywood Latina: Race, Sex, and Stardom|url=https://archive.org/details/dancehollywoodla0000oval|url-access=registration|year=2011|publisher=Rutgers University Press|isbn=978-0813548807|pages=[https://archive.org/details/dancehollywoodla0000oval/page/3 3–4]}}</ref> Troy Patterson of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' also observed that she used her body for emphasis on stage, "She turned herself out as the fly girl hyperversion of postfeminist power, flaunting her control by toying with the threat of excess. In consequence, her star went supernova."<ref>{{cite news|last=Patterson|first=Troy|title=Rock Frock|url=https://ew.com/ew/article/0,,92259,00.html|work=Entertainment Weekly |access-date=June 30, 2013|date=December 19, 2000}}</ref> Her signature movements include "clock-wise pivoting with salsa hip circles and sequential torso undulations".<ref>{{cite book|last=Potuoglu-Cook|first=Oyku|title=Night Shifts: Moral, Economic, and Cultural Politics of Turkish Belly Dance|year=2008|isbn=978-0549541301|page=167}}</ref> While being noted to lip sync in the early stages of career, Lopez's Dance Again World Tour was praised for showcasing live vocals and choreography synchronously.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lip syncing takes the fun out of seeing an artist live|newspaper=Contra Costa Times|date=June 21, 2002}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Fuller |first=Bonnie |url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2012/12/05/jennifer-lopez-dance-again-tour-divorce-marc-anthony/ |title=Jennifer Lopez 'Dance Again' Tour — Why She Had to Divorce Marc Anthony |publisher=Hollywood Life |date=December 5, 2012 |access-date=May 31, 2013}}</ref><ref name="filipino">{{cite web|last=Concepcion|first=Pocholo|title=JLo enchants capacity crowd at MOA Arena concert|url=http://entertainment.inquirer.net/69407/jlo-enchants-capacity-crowd-at-moa-arena-concert|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |access-date=November 27, 2012|date=November 27, 2012}}</ref> In a review of her Las Vegas residency All I Have, ''Los Angeles Times'' writer Nolan Feeney remarked that her dancing is "undoubtedly the centerpiece of the show".<ref name="LA Times Vegas" />

Lopez's provocative stage performances have also drawn scrutiny at times. In May 2013, her performance on the finale of the television series ''[[Britain's Got Talent]]'' was deemed inappropriate for family-friendly television, and drew viewer complaints to [[Ofcom]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.digitalspy.com.au/british-tv/s107/britains-got-talent/news/a486003/jennifer-lopez-britains-got-talent-producers-said-to-wear-outfit.html |title=Jennifer Lopez: 'Britain's Got Talent producers said to wear outfit' |work=Digital Spy |access-date=May 31, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130604123052/http://www.digitalspy.com.au/british-tv/s107/britains-got-talent/news/a486003/jennifer-lopez-britains-got-talent-producers-said-to-wear-outfit.html |archive-date=June 4, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Following her controversial performance at the musical festival [[Mawazine]] in 2015, Moroccan Prime Minister [[Abdelilah Benkirane]] called it "indecent" and "disgraceful", while an education group claimed that she "disturbed public order and tarnished women's honor and respect".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Shepherd|first1=Jack|title=Jennifer Lopez concert: Moroccan PM demands investigation into 'provocative' performance|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/jennifer-lopez-moroccan-pm-demands-investigation-into-provocative-performance-10304831.html|website=[[The Independent]]|access-date=November 23, 2016|date=June 8, 2015}}</ref>

==Public image==
[[File:Jennifer Lopez Spring Summer.jpg|thumb|left|upright|200px|Lopez wearing an updated version of her iconic [[Green Versace dress of Jennifer Lopez|green Versace dress]] at [[Milan Fashion Week]] in September 2019]]

Speaking of Lopez's image, Andrew Barker of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' observed: "Despite a carefully cultivated image as an imperious pop empress in ludicrously expensive outfits, her signature hits bear the titles "I'm Real" and "Jenny From the Block". She managed the perilous transition from actress to music star without ever seeming to pick either as a primary gig. She established herself as an oft-provocative sex symbol while her demeanor made it abundantly clear that she's not asking you to come hither."<ref name="Variety">{{cite news|last=Barker|first=Andrew|title=Jennifer Lopez Receives Star for Music on Hollywood Walk of Fame|url=https://variety.com/2013/scene/features/jennifer-lopez-receives-star-for-music-on-hollywood-walk-of-fame-1200493728/|work=Variety |access-date=June 25, 2013|date=June 20, 2013}}</ref> In 2002, Lynette Holloway of ''[[The New York Times]]'' described Lopez as overexposed. She wrote: "Forgive yourself if you are seeing Jennifer Lopez in your sleep. She is everywhere." Holloway noted her image to be "a dash of ''ghetto fabulousness''" and "middle-class respectability" for mass appeal.<ref>{{cite news |last=Holloway|first=Lynette|title=Keeping J. Lo in Spotlight Has Risks for Her Career As Well as Rich Rewards|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=December 9, 2002|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/12/09/business/keeping-j-lo-in-spotlight-has-risks-for-her-career-as-well-as-rich-rewards.html|access-date=June 30, 2013}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' observed a change in her public profile upon joining ''American Idol'' in 2011, writing: "Gone was her old cut-a-bitch swagger; J. Lo 2.0 is an all-embracing, [[Oprah Winfrey|Oprah]]fied earth ''{{Linktext|madre}}''."<ref>{{cite web|last1=Markovitz|first1=Adam|title=Love? review – Jennifer Lopez|url=https://ew.com/article/2011/05/04/love-review-jennifer-lopez-music-ewcom|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=November 20, 2016|date=May 4, 2011}}</ref> Lopez is considered an [[pop icon|icon of popular culture]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2005/10/prweb298759.htm |title=The Biggest Latin Vibe Sweeping America Is Up for Sale? |publisher=PRWeb |access-date=November 12, 2012}}</ref> Television presenter [[Ray Martin (television presenter)|Ray Martin]] describes her as a "showbiz phenomenon".<ref>{{cite web|last=Martin|first=Ray|title=J-Lo|url=http://sixtyminutes.ninemsn.com.au/stories/raymartin/304846/j-lo|access-date=February 28, 2012|date=October 11, 2007|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120410062535/http://sixtyminutes.ninemsn.com.au/stories/raymartin/304846/j-lo|archive-date=April 10, 2012}}</ref>

Lopez is widely celebrated for her [[Venus Callipyge|callipygian figure]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sir Mix-A-Lot Says 'Baby Got Back' Is About Jennifer Lopez|url=https://www.spin.com/2014/11/sir-mix-a-lot-says-baby-got-back-is-about-jennifer-lopez/|website=Spin|publisher=SpinMedia|access-date=January 4, 2015|date=November 13, 2014}}</ref> She has been credited with influencing a change in mainstream female [[body image]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Mi Voz, Mi Vida/ My Voice, My Life: Latino College Students Tell Their Life Stories|year=2007|publisher=Cornwell University Press|isbn=978-0801473869|page=179|author1=Andrew Garrod |author2=Robert Kilkenny |author3=Christina Gómez }}</ref> In ''Latin Sensations'' (2001), Herón Marquez wrote: "Because she wasn't rail thin, Lopez had broken the mold and allowed millions of women to feel good about their bodies. Suddenly, it was okay for women to have hips, curves, and a big backside."<ref name="Latin Sensations" /> ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'' described her buttocks as "in and of themselves, a cultural icon".<ref>{{cite news|title=Marisa Meltzer:For Posteriors' Sake|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/18/fashion/more-women-seeking-curvaceous-posteriors.html|date=September 17, 2014}}</ref> [[Details (magazine)|''Details'']] magazine named Lopez the "Sexiest Woman of the Year" in 1998,<ref>{{cite news|last=Halza|first=George Halza|title=Jennifer Lopez named sexiest woman of the year|newspaper=[[Reading Eagle]]|date=November 16, 1998|page=5}}</ref> and she led ''[[FHM]]''{{'}}s "[[FHM's 100 Sexiest Women (UK)|100 Sexiest Women]]" list twice.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/jennifer-lopez |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081216065613/http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/jennifer-lopez |url-status=dead |archive-date=December 16, 2008 |title=''FHM'' – Jennifer Lopez |work=FHM |access-date=March 10, 2012 }}</ref> In 2011, she was named "[[People Magazine's 100 Most Beautiful People|The Most Beautiful Woman]]" by [[People (American magazine)|''People'']].<ref>{{cite news |last=Jordan|first=Julie|title=Jennifer Lopez: Being Beautiful Is 'Part of My Job'|url=http://www.people.com/people/package/article/0,,20360857_20481259,00.html |work=People |access-date=January 29, 2012|date=April 13, 2011}}</ref> The following year, [[VH1]] ranked her the fourth on their list of "100 Sexiest Artists",<ref>{{cite web|author=Bené Viera |url=http://www.vh1.com/music/tuner/2013-03-05/vh1-100-sexiest-artists-complete-list/97/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130313093239/http://www.vh1.com/music/tuner/2013-03-05/vh1-100-sexiest-artists-complete-list/97 |url-status=dead |archive-date=March 13, 2013 |title=VH1's 100 Sexiest Artists [Complete List&#93; – &#124; VH1 Tuner |publisher=VH-1 |date=March 5, 2013 |access-date=April 19, 2013 }}</ref> while [[Vibe (magazine)|''Vibe'']] magazine named her the most "lustable" celebrity of the past twenty years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vibe.com/article/big-list-issue-19-most-lustable-celebs-93 |title=The 19 Most Lustable Celebs Since '93 |work=Vibe |date=April 17, 2013 |access-date=May 31, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130520234051/http://www.vibe.com/article/big-list-issue-19-most-lustable-celebs-93 |archive-date=May 20, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2014, Lopez stated, "There's this funny notion in America that you can't be a mom and be sexy (...) It's the craziest thing I've ever heard... The truth is that women can be sexy until the day they die."<ref name="HuffPost Latino"/>

Lopez has been a [[Tabloid journalism|tabloid]] fixture<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lansky|first1=Sam|title=Jennifer Lopez Is Back On Top With 'Love?' Which Is Exactly Where She Deserves To Be|url=http://buzzworthy.mtv.com/2012/04/19/jennifer-lopez-love-on-the-floor-dance-again/|access-date=January 28, 2015|publisher=[[MTV]]|date=April 19, 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402110709/http://buzzworthy.mtv.com/2012/04/19/jennifer-lopez-love-on-the-floor-dance-again/|archive-date=April 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Johnson|first1=Steve|title=Will Lopez, Tyler be good for 'American Idol'?|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2010-09-22/entertainment/chi-100922-american-idol-judges-strengths_1_kara-dioguardi-steven-tyler-classic-rock|access-date=January 28, 2015|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|date=September 22, 2010}}</ref> and has admitted to having a "less-than-perfect" public image.<ref>{{cite web|last=Saney|first=Daniel|title=J.Lo blames films for bad public image|url=https://www.digitalspy.com.au/showbiz/news/a19076/jlo-blames-films-for-bad-public-image.html|work=Digital Spy|access-date=June 26, 2013|date=February 8, 2005|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130920183528/http://www.digitalspy.com.au/showbiz/news/a19076/jlo-blames-films-for-bad-public-image.html|archive-date=September 20, 2013|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The media has drawn comparisons between Lopez and actress [[Elizabeth Taylor]], due to her numerous failed relationships,<ref>{{cite news|title=Vibe Media Group|date=July 2003|work=Vibe|issue=7|volume=11|issn=1070-4701}}</ref> and Lopez has been dubbed a "modern-day Liz Taylor" by the media.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lopez doesn't mind Liz link|newspaper=The Age|date=December 27, 2002}}</ref> Lynn Hirschberg of ''[[W (magazine)|W]]'' compared her glamorous public persona to that of Taylor.<ref name="W2013">{{cite web|last=Hirschberg|first=Lynn|title=Jennifer Lopez: Dream Girl|url=http://www.wmagazine.com/people/celebrities/2013/07/jennifer-lopez-august-2013-cover/|work=W|access-date=July 10, 2013|date=July 9, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130711103336/http://www.wmagazine.com/people/celebrities/2013/07/jennifer-lopez-august-2013-cover|archive-date=July 11, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Her style was described by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''{{'}}s Lauren Savage as "scantily clad".<ref name="Scla">{{cite web|last=Savage|first=Lauren|title=J.Lo Plays Gender-Bending Boxer for V Magazine Cover|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-hook/502987/jlo-plays-gender-bending-boxer-for-v-magazine-cover|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=August 20, 2012|date=February 29, 2012}}</ref> She has received a bad reputation as being a demanding "diva",<ref>{{cite news |title=Demanding diva Jennifer Lopez bans domestic staff from speaking to her|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/demanding-diva-jennifer-lopez-bans-domestic-staff-from-speaking-to-her-8134190.html|work=[[London Evening Standard]]|access-date=January 8, 2013|date=September 13, 2012}}</ref> something which she denies.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Brant |first1=Emma |title=Jennifer Lopez denies diva demands in US interview |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/26559585/jennifer-lopez-denies-diva-demands-in-us-interview |website=[[BBC]] |access-date=February 1, 2020 |date=March 13, 2014}}</ref> In 2003, ''[[The Observer]]'' remarked that Lopez was "the woman immortalised in a million headlines as 'Hollywood's most demanding diva' ... Lopez must wonder what heinous crime she has committed to become the most vilified woman in modern popular culture."<ref name="SMH 2007">{{cite news|title=Let's get loud, Latina and proud|url=https://www.smh.com.au/news/music/lets-get-loud-latina-and-proud/2007/04/15/1176575667884.html?page=4|newspaper=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|date=April 16, 2007|access-date=January 23, 2017}}</ref>

==Legacy and cultural impact==

[[File:Jennifer Lopez with Flag.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Lopez waving the [[Flag of Puerto Rico|Puerto Rican flag]] in 2009 at the [[Puerto Rican Day Parade]] in [[Manhattan]]]]
Lopez is regarded as the most influential Latin performer in North America, credited with breaking ethnic barriers in the entertainment industry.<ref name=rantrack /><ref name=leading1 /> In 1999, ''[[The Record (Waterloo Region)|The Record]]'' newspaper observed that she was responsible for the introduction of a Latina presence in the film industry, which was a "whites-only preserve" for much of its history.<ref name=therecord>{{cite news |last=Pearlman|first=Cindy|title=For the record; Very hot and ambitious actress Jennifer Lopez has music on her mind|newspaper=[[The Record (Waterloo Region)|The Record]] |issn=0824-5150|date=August 14, 1999|location=Kitchener, Ontario}}</ref> Described as a "multidimensional artist who had turned into a financial powerhouse",<ref name="hhh">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZXRcV6k0F9sC&pg=PA221 |title=Icons of American Popular Culture: From P.T. Barnum to Jennifer Lopez |author=Robert C. Cottrell |publisher=M.E. Sharpe |page=221 |year=2009 |access-date=March 10, 2012|isbn=978-0-7656-2835-0}}</ref> Lopez became the highest-paid actress of Hispanic descent in history.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez - Biography|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/304444/jennifer-lopez/biography|website=Billboard|access-date=November 19, 2016|archive-date=February 2, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202231211/http://www.billboard.com/artist/304444/jennifer-lopez/biography|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Miriam Jiménez Román]] stated in ''The Afro-Latin Reader: History and Culture in the United States'' (2009) that "[she] was able to traverse the difficult racial boundaries".<ref>{{cite book|title=The Afro-Latin@ Reader: History and Culture in the United States|year=2009|publisher=Duke Press|isbn=978-0822391319|page=532|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mSJpaNVnazQC&q=Jennifer+Lopez+Latin&pg=PT548|author1=Miriam Jiménez Román |author2=Juan Flores |access-date=July 2, 2013}}</ref> In 2012, business magazine ''[[Forbes]]'' suggested that Lopez "may be the most powerful entertainer on the planet",<ref>{{cite news|last=Casserly|first=Meghan|title=The 10 Most Talked About Women of 2012|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/meghancasserly/2012/12/13/hillary-clinton-beyonce-10-most-talked-about-women-of-2012/|work=Forbes |access-date=August 10, 2013|date=December 13, 2012}}</ref> and named her "the world's most powerful Latino celebrity".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Antunes|first1=Anderson|title=The World's Most Powerful Latino Celebrities|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2012/05/25/the-worlds-most-powerful-latino-celebrities/|access-date=December 6, 2015|work=Forbes |date=May 25, 2012}}</ref>

Upon launching her music career in the late 1990s, Lopez contributed to the "Latin explosion" occurring in entertainment at the time.<ref>{{cite news |last=Tarradell|first=Mario|title=Latin aftershocks Music's ethnic boom reshapes the Grammy landscape|newspaper=The Dallas Morning News|date=February 20, 2000}}</ref> Writing for [[The Recording Academy]], Brian Haack described her as the "breakout female star" of the [[Latin American music in the United States#1990s Latin Explosion|Latin pop movement]] in American music.<ref name="Recording Academy 2017">{{cite web |last1=Haack |first1=Brian |title=1999: The Year Latin Pop Conquered America |url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/news/1999-year-latin-pop-conquered-america |publisher=[[The Recording Academy]] |access-date=June 17, 2018 |date=October 6, 2017}}</ref> She was featured on the cover of the first issue of ''[[Latina (magazine)|Latina]]'' magazine in 1996, with editor Galina Espinoza stating in 2011 that there is "no recounting of modern Latina history without Jennifer".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Espinoza|first1=Galina|title=Lessons Learned From 15 Years of Jennifer Lopez|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/galina-espinoza/lessons-learned-from-15-y_b_957796.html|website=[[The Huffington Post]]|access-date=May 25, 2018|date=September 12, 2011}}</ref> Around the time her career began to burgeon, the emphasis on Lopez's curvaceous figure grew; scholar Sean Redmond wrote that this was a sign of her role and social power in the cultural changes occurring in the United States.<ref>{{harvnb|Redmond|2007|pp=282–283}}</ref> In August 2005, ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' listed Lopez as one of the most influential Hispanics in America, remarking: "Why? Because over a decade ago, she was an anonymous background dancer on the second-rated sketch-comedy show. Today she's known by two syllables."<ref name="timeTyrangiel" /> In February 2007, ''[[People en Español]]'' named her the most influential Hispanic entertainer.<ref name=leading1>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/peopleNews/idUSN0417833620070105|title=J.Lo tops list of most influential Hispanics|access-date=February 12, 2007|work=Reuters |date=January 4, 2007}}</ref> In 2014, scientists named a species of aquatic [[mite]] found in Puerto Rico, ''[[Litarachna lopezae]]'', after Lopez.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2014/jul/17/scientists-name-new-species-of-water-mite-after-jennifer-lopez |title=Scientists name new species of water mite after Jennifer Lopez |author=Harriet Gibsone |date=July 17, 2014 |website=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=July 19, 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/celebrity/ls-celebrity-news/puerto-rican-water-mite-named-after-jennifer-lopez-20140717-ztu05.html |title=Puerto Rican water mite named after Jennifer Lopez |author=Danica Coto |date=July 17, 2014 |website=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |access-date=July 19, 2014 }}</ref>

Lopez is considered a global icon, and is often described as a [[Triple threat (entertainer)|triple threat]] performer.<ref name="BBMAs 2014">{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez to Receive Icon Award and Perform at BBMAs|url=http://www.billboardmusicawards.com/2014/05/jennifer-lopez-to-receive-icon-award-and-perform-at-bbmas/|publisher=[[Billboard Music Awards]]|access-date=January 10, 2020|date=May 5, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161124091443/http://www.billboardmusicawards.com/2014/05/jennifer-lopez-to-receive-icon-award-and-perform-at-bbmas/|archive-date=November 24, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="People Magazine Awards">{{cite web|last1=Steiner|first1=Amanda Michelle|title=PEOPLE Magazine Awards: Jennifer Lopez Wins Triple Threat Award|url=http://people.com/awards/jennifer-lopez-at-the-people-magazine-awards-wins-triple-threat-award/|website=People|access-date=January 10, 2020|date=December 18, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Time Review">{{cite news|last1=Feeney|first1=Nolan|title=Review: Jennifer Lopez's New Residency Turns Las Vegas Into Destination Diva|url=http://time.com/4217043/jennifer-lopezs-new-show-turns-las-vegas-into-destination-diva/|website=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|access-date=January 10, 2020|date=February 11, 2016}}</ref>  [[VH1]] ranked her at number 15 on their list of [[The Greatest (TV series)|200 Greatest Pop Culture Icons]],<ref>{{cite news|title=The 200 Greatest Pop Culture Icons Complete Ranked List|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/the-200-greatest-pop-culture-icons-complete-ranked-list-70807437.html|agency=PR Newswire|access-date=June 30, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170501100900/http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/the-200-greatest-pop-culture-icons-complete-ranked-list-70807437.html|archive-date=May 1, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> number 16 on 100 Greatest Women In Music,<ref>{{cite web|last=Graham |first=Mark |title=VH1's 100 Greatest Women In Music |url=http://www.vh1.com/music/tuner/2012-02-13/vh1s-100-greatest-women-in-music-complete-list/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120214233543/http://www.vh1.com/music/tuner/2012-02-13/vh1s-100-greatest-women-in-music-complete-list/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=February 14, 2012 |publisher=[[VH1]] |access-date=February 29, 2012 |date=February 13, 2012 }}</ref> and number 21 on 50 Greatest Women of the Video Era.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vh1.com/shows/the_greatest/episode.jhtml?episodeID=66355 |title=Ep. 071 &#124; 50 Greatest Women of the Video Era |publisher=VH1 |access-date=August 10, 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629061423/http://www.vh1.com/shows/the_greatest/episode.jhtml?episodeID=66355 |archive-date=June 29, 2011 }}</ref> Lopez has been cited as an influence or inspiration by a range of entertainers, including [[Jessica Alba]],<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tewari|first1=Nidhi|title=Jessica Alba Talks About Her Entrepreneurial Side, Says She Considers Jennifer Lopez As Her Idol|url=http://www.ibtimes.com.au/jessica-alba-talks-about-her-entrepreneurial-side-says-she-considers-jennifer-lopez-her-idol-1370954|website=[[International Business Times]]|access-date=September 19, 2014|date=September 18, 2014}}</ref> [[Adrienne Bailon]],<ref name="Latina 2013" /> [[Kat DeLuna]],<ref name="DeLuna">{{cite news|title=J.Lo's new song sounds suspiciously like one from Hispanic hottie Kat DeLuna|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2011-01-19/gossip/27087962_1_jlo-kat-deluna-similarities|work=Daily News|location=New York |access-date=February 4, 2012|date=January 19, 2011}}</ref> [[Mike Doughty]],<ref name="dep13">{{cite web|last=Letkemman|first=Jessica|title=Mike Doughty Opens 'Book of Drugs,' Says J.Lo & Music Thieves Saved His Life|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/464820/mike-doughty-opens-book-of-drugs-says-jlo-music-thieves-saved-his-life|work=Billboard |access-date=February 26, 2012|location=New York|date=December 7, 2011}}</ref> [[Fifth Harmony]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teennick.com/blog/teennick-top-10-an-interview-with-fifth-harmony.html |title=TeenNick Top 10: An Interview With Fifth Harmony |work=[[Teen Nick]] |date=August 22, 2013 |access-date=March 28, 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130822150229/http://www.teennick.com/blog/teennick-top-10-an-interview-with-fifth-harmony.html |archive-date=August 22, 2013 }}</ref> [[Becky G]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/becky-g-talks-working-with-jennifer-lopez-i-still-get-goosebumps-when-i-watch-the-video_article_78034 |title=Becky G Talks Working With Jennifer Lopez: 'I Still Get Goosebumps When I Watch The Video' |publisher=Accesshollywood.com |date=April 14, 2013 |access-date=April 19, 2013}}</ref> [[Selena Gomez]],<ref name=SelenaGomez>{{cite news | url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2012/06/08/selena-gomez-gets-racy-in-elle-photoshoot/ | publisher=Fox News Latino | title=Selena Gomez Gets Racy in 'Elle' Photoshoot | date=June 8, 2012 | access-date=December 22, 2018 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160624114525/http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2012/06/08/selena-gomez-gets-racy-in-elle-photoshoot/ | archive-date=June 24, 2016 | url-status=dead | df=mdy-all }}</ref> [[Ryan Guzman]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Ryan Guzman pushed by 'inspirational' Jennifer Lopez|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/news/ryan-guzman-pushed-by-inspirational-jennifer-lopez-35266903.html|website=[[The Belfast Telegraph]]|access-date=December 6, 2016|date=December 4, 2016|archive-date=December 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220084909/http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/news/ryan-guzman-pushed-by-inspirational-jennifer-lopez-35266903.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Kelly Key]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universomusical.com.br/materia.asp?mt=sim&id=170&cod=po|title=Kelly Key busca o sucesso de Christina Aguilera, Jennifer Lopez, Britney Spears, Madonna e Janet Jackson|work=Universo Musical|access-date=January 7, 2012|archive-date=March 7, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307031750/http://universomusical.com.br/materia.asp?cod=po&id=170&mt=sim|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Q'orianka Kilcher]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crushable.com/2008/09/19/entertainment/flashback-qorianka-kilcher-thanks-j-lo-at-the-alma-awards/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105220340/http://www.crushable.com/2008/09/19/entertainment/flashback-qorianka-kilcher-thanks-j-lo-at-the-alma-awards/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=November 5, 2013 |title=Flashback: Q'orianka Kilcher Thanks J-Lo at the Alma Awards |publisher=Crushable |date=September 19, 2008 |access-date=April 19, 2013 }}</ref> [[Demi Lovato]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Demi Lovato inspired by Jennifer Lopez|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/music/demi-lovato-inspired-by-jennifer-lopez/|website=[[The Indian Express]] |access-date=September 21, 2015|date=March 6, 2015}}</ref> [[Normani]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Viswanath|first1=Jake|title=Normani Is Finally Stepping Out On Her Own|url=https://vmagazine.com/article/normani-finally-stepping/|website=[[V (American magazine)|V]]|access-date=March 6, 2018|date=February 14, 2018}}</ref> [[Rita Ora]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Rita Ora ‘inspired’ by Jennifer Lopez and Beyonce |url=https://apnews.com/article/aa11c32f41644b8eb5071c7f2887bb83 |website=[[Associated Press]] |access-date=June 14, 2021 |date=April 19, 2018}}</ref> [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Kit|first=Zorianna|title=Pitbull on music, Jennifer Lopez and 'Epic'|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/pitbull-on-music-jennifer-lopez-and-epic/2013/05/23/bc108dbc-c314-11e2-914f-a7aba60512a7_story.html|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |access-date=May 26, 2013|date=May 26, 2013}}</ref> [[Francia Raisa]],<ref name="Latina 2013">{{cite web|last1=Rodriguez|first1=Priscilla|title=10 Stars J.Lo Influenced|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/stars-celebrities-jennifer-lopez-influenced|website=[[Latina (magazine)|Latina]] |access-date=December 8, 2015|date=August 31, 2013}}</ref> [[Naya Rivera]],<ref>{{cite news |last=Cosgrove |first=Sheila |url=https://people.com/tv/naya-rivera-hopes-to-follow-in-jennifer-lopezs-footsteps/|title=Naya Rivera Hopes to Follow in Jennifer Lopez's Footsteps|work=People |date=September 6, 2013|access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref> [[Bebe Rexha]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Schiller|first=Rebecca|title=Bebe Rexha Talks New Album 'Expectations,' Her Love of Jennifer Lopez at Billboard Music Awards: Watch|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/8457118/bebe-rexha-billboard-music-awards-video-interview|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=May 25, 2018|date=May 21, 2018}}</ref> [[Rosa Salazar]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://us.hola.com/celebrities/2019020819950/rosa-salazar-alita-battle-angel-hola-usa-interview/ |title=ALITA: BATTLE ANGEL'S ROSA SALAZAR ON FLYING THE NEST AT 15 TO LEADING THIS STAR-STUDDED LATINX CAST |author=AliSandra Puliti |date=February 8, 2019 |website=Hola!}}</ref> [[Gwen Stefani]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mahjouri|first1=Shakiel|title=Gwen Stefani Admits 'I'm Obviously At The End Of My Journey Of Being A Musician'|url=https://etcanada.com/news/330123/gwen-stefani-admits-im-obviously-at-the-end-of-my-journey-of-being-a-musician/|website=[[Entertainment Tonight Canada]]|access-date=May 25, 2018|date=May 21, 2018}}</ref> [[Stooshe]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.digitalspy.com.au/music/news/a502912/j-lo-trains-in-hair-and-make-up-for-an-hour-before-shows-say-stooshe.html |title=J-Lo trains in hair and make-up for an hour before shows, say Stooshe |work=Digital Spy |date=August 1, 2013 |access-date=August 10, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131106045025/http://www.digitalspy.com.au/music/news/a502912/j-lo-trains-in-hair-and-make-up-for-an-hour-before-shows-say-stooshe.html |archive-date=November 6, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> and [[Kerry Washington]].<ref name="KW1">{{cite news |title=Kerry Washington: Lopez inspired me |url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/news/kerry-washington-lopez-inspired-me-16111987.html |newspaper=The Belfast Telegraph |access-date=February 4, 2012 |date=February 1, 2012 |archive-date=February 4, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120204122210/http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/news/kerry-washington-lopez-inspired-me-16111987.html |url-status=dead }}</ref>

In 2019, the [[Council of Fashion Designers of America]] presented her with its Fashion Icon Award for her "long-standing and global impact on fashion".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bateman |first1=Kristen |title=CFDA Fashion Awards 2019: Jennifer Lopez and Barbie among winners |url=https://edition.cnn.com/style/article/cfda-fashion-awards-2019/index.html |publisher=[[CNN]] |access-date=July 20, 2019 |date=June 4, 2019}}</ref> The [[Green Versace dress of Jennifer Lopez|Green Versace "Jungle Dress"]] that Lopez wore at the [[42nd Annual Grammy Awards]] in 2000 was voted the fifth most iconic [[Red carpet fashion|red carpet dress]] of all time in a poll run by ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]''.<ref name="Telegraph08">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/3167702/Liz-Hurley-safety-pin-dress-voted-the-greatest-dress.html|author=Urmee Khan|title=Liz Hurley 'safety pin' dress voted the greatest dress |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=October 9, 2008|access-date=May 1, 2011|location=London}}</ref> The images of Lopez wearing the dress became the most popular search query of all time at that point, and subsequently led to the creation of [[Google Search|Google]]'s [[Image retrieval|image search]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Schmidt|first1=Eric |author-link=Eric Schmidt |title=The Tinker's Apprentice|url=http://www.project-syndicate.org/commentary/google-european-commission-and-disruptive-technological-change-by-eric-schmidt-2015-01 |publisher=Project-syndicate.org|access-date=January 25, 2015|date=January 19, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2015/04/08/j-los-infamous-green-grammys-dress-is-the-reason-google-images-exists/77568210/|title=J.Lo's infamous green Grammys dress is the reason Google Images exists|newspaper=USA Today|access-date=February 12, 2017|language=en}}</ref> Her style has influenced a range of celebrities, including [[Kelly Rowland]], [[Kim Kardashian]], and [[Jennifer Love Hewitt]].<ref name="styleicons">{{cite web|url=http://photos.essence.com/galleries/kelly_rowland__style_icons|title=Kelly Rowland: Style Icons|work=Essence|access-date=May 12, 2012|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6BY3cv3cs?url=http://photos.essence.com/galleries/kelly_rowland__style_icons|archive-date=October 20, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="kimj">{{cite web|last=Coughlan|first=Maggie|title=Kim Kardashian Considers Jennifer Lopez a Style Icon|url=http://www.popeater.com/2011/02/15/kim-kardashian-qvc-fashion-week/|publisher=PopEater|access-date=January 10, 2012|date=February 15, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110824073534/http://www.popeater.com/2011/02/15/kim-kardashian-qvc-fashion-week/|archive-date=August 24, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Harp|first=Justin|title=Jennifer Love Hewitt: 'Jennifer Lopez's style is amazing'|url=https://www.digitalspy.com.au/showbiz/news/a470919/jennifer-love-hewitt-jennifer-lopezs-style-is-amazing.html|work=Digital Spy|access-date=April 9, 2013|date=April 6, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130520091834/http://www.digitalspy.com.au/showbiz/news/a470919/jennifer-love-hewitt-jennifer-lopezs-style-is-amazing.html|archive-date=May 20, 2013|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Her record-breaking fragrance line has become the most successful celebrity line in the world, with sales exceeding $2 billion {{as of|2012|lc=y}}.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/jennifer-lopez-and-nuvotv-announce-exclusive-creative-production-and-marketing-partnership-169416666.html |title=Jennifer Lopez and nuvoTV Announce Exclusive Creative, Production and Marketing Partnership |location=Los Angeles |date=September 12, 2012 |agency=PR Newswire |access-date=July 20, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140906133814/http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/jennifer-lopez-and-nuvotv-announce-exclusive-creative-production-and-marketing-partnership-169416666.html |archive-date=September 6, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Her first fragrance, [[Glow by JLo]], has been credited with influencing the rise of celebrity fragrances in the 2000s,<ref name="WWD">{{cite web|last=Naughton|first=Julie|title=Getting to the Heart of J.Lo|url=http://www.wwd.com/beauty-industry-news/people/jennifer-lopez-maintains-foothold-in-fragrance-5642440?page=2|work=[[Women's Wear Daily|WWD]]|access-date=October 21, 2012|date=February 9, 2012}}</ref> with perfume critic [[Chandler Burr]] stating: "[[Elizabeth Taylor]] was one of the first [to have her own scent], but Glow kicked the whole thing into overdrive."<ref>{{cite web |last1=McIntosh |first1=Steven |title=Is this the end of celebrity fragrances? |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-38756997 |website=[[BBC News]] |access-date=July 5, 2018 |date=February 28, 2017}}</ref> Following the success of Lopez's appointment as a judge on ''[[American Idol]]'' in 2010, a trend of networks hiring "big names" for judging panels on reality shows ensued. ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' branded this "The J.Lo Effect".<ref>{{cite web|title=The J.Lo Effect: $15 Million Becoming the New Standard as Reality Salaries Soar|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/reality-salaries-american-idol-jennifer-lopez-howard-stern-290871|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=July 4, 2013|author=Lacey Rose, Shirley Halperin|date=February 15, 2012}}</ref>

==Achievements==
{{See also|List of awards and nominations received by Jennifer Lopez}}

{{as of|2017}}, Lopez has sold more than 70 million records worldwide,<ref>{{cite web |title=Top 10 hits of Jennifer Lopez |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/english/hollywood/photo-features/top-10-hits-of-jennifer-lopez/photostory/59772602.cms |website=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref> and her films have grossed a cumulative total of {{US$|3.1{{nbsp}}billion}}.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez Movie Box Office Results|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/people/chart/?id=jenniferlopez.htm|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|access-date=December 14, 2017|quote=Total: $3,057.7 million}}</ref> She remains the only female entertainer to have a number one album and film simultaneously in the United States.<ref>{{cite news |title=Billboard 200|work=Billboard|date=February 10, 2001|volume= 113| issue = 6|page=88|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ghMEAAAAMBAJ&q=Jennifer+Lopez+J.Lo|access-date=April 13, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Karlin|first1=Lily|title=5 Things You Didn't Know About Jennifer Lopez|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com.au/entry/things-you-didnt-know-jennifer-lopez_us_55b12215e4b08f57d5d3e6cc|newspaper=[[HuffPost]]|publisher=[[AOL]]|access-date=November 19, 2016|date=July 24, 2015}}</ref>
With her second studio album ''J.Lo'' (2001), Lopez became the first female solo recording artist under [[Epic Records]] to achieve a number one album in the United States since its inception in 1953.<ref>{{cite news|title=Billboard 200|newspaper=Billboard|date=February 10, 2001|volume= 113| issue = 6|page=94|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ghMEAAAAMBAJ&q=Jennifer+Lopez+J.Lo|access-date=April 13, 2013}}</ref> Her album ''J to tha L-O! The Remixes'' was acknowledged by the ''[[Guinness World Records]]'' as the first number one [[remix]] album in the United States.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3186761.stm |title=Diaz tops actress pay list |access-date=April 18, 2009 |date=August 27, 2004 |work=BBC News}}</ref> In 2010, Lopez was honored by the [[World Music Awards]] with the Legend Award for her contribution to the arts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hola.com/musica/2010051914399/world/music/awards/|title=Jennifer López, premiada por toda su carrera en los World Music Awards|website=www.hola.com}}{{Dead link|date=May 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Lopez's return to prominence the following year with her single "On the Floor"—among the [[List of best-selling singles|best-selling singles of all time]], and its music video recognized as the "Highest Viewed Female Music Video of All Time" by ''Guinness World Records'' in 2012—is regarded as one of the greatest musical comebacks in history.<ref name=comeback>{{cite news|last=Kennedy|first=Gerrick D.|title=Jennifer Lopez named 'world's greatest musical comeback act' – seriously|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2011/12/jennifer-lopez-named-worlds-greatest-musical-comeback-act-seriously.html|work=Los Angeles Times |access-date=January 29, 2012|date=December 13, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Rodriguez|first1=Priscilla|title=7 Latino Celebrities With Guinness World Records|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/celebrity/latino-celebrities-stars-guinness-world-records#6|website=Latina |access-date=December 5, 2015|date=September 19, 2014}}</ref> In 2013, she was presented with the prestigious landmark 2,500th star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]] for her musical contributions,<ref>{{cite news|last=Johnson|first=Reed|title=Jennifer Lopez, new Walk of Famer, cites Fonda among role models|url=https://latimes.com/entertainment/music/posts/la-et-ms-jennifer-lopez-gets-star-on-hollywood-walk-of-fame-20130623,0,4699689.story|work=Los Angeles Times |access-date=June 26, 2013|date=June 23, 2013}}</ref> and [[Univision]] presented her with the World Icon Award in its [[2013 Premios Juventud|Premios Juventud]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Baida|first1=Aiyana|title=Jennifer Lopez Wins Premios Juventud's World Icon Award (Video)|url=https://huffingtonpost.com/2013/07/19/jennifer-lopez-premios-juventud_n_3622993.html%7D|website=[[HuffPost]]|access-date=November 19, 2016|date=July 19, 2013}}</ref> In 2014, she became the first female recipient of the [[Billboard Icon Award]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ramirez|first1=Erika|title=Jennifer Lopez Receives Icon Award, Performs 'First Love' at the 2014 Billboard Music Awards|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/bbma-2014/6092051/jennifer-lopez-icon-award-billboard-music-awards|work=Billboard |access-date=December 6, 2015|date=May 18, 2014}}</ref> ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine ranked her as the ninth greatest [[Dance Club Songs|dance club]] artist of all time in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Greatest of All Time Top Dance Club Artists|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-top-dance-club-artists|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=September 28, 2017}}</ref> In 2017, she was awarded the [[Telemundo]] Star Award.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nicky Jam Wins Big at Billboard Latin Music Awards: See the Full Winners List|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/latin-awards/7776260/billboard-latin-music-awards-2017-winners-list|date=April 27, 2017}}</ref> In 2018, Lopez received the [[Michael Jackson Video Vanguard Award]] at the [[2018 MTV Video Music Awards]], making her the first Latin performer to claim the prize since its introduction in 1984.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dresdale |first1=Andrea |title=Jennifer Lopez to receive Michael Jackson Video Vanguard Award at MTV VMAs |url=http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2018/7/31/jennifer-lopez-to-receive-michael-jackson-video-vanguard-awa.html |publisher=[[ABC News Radio]] |access-date=August 2, 2018 |date=July 31, 2018}}</ref>

{{Clear}}

